var VERSES_ACTS=[{"ref":"Acts 1:1","short":"Ac 1:1","text":"In the first book, O Theophilus, I have dealt with all that Jesus began to do and teach,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 1:2","short":"Ac 1:2","text":"until the day when he was taken up, after he had given commands through the Holy Spirit to the apostles whom he had chosen.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 1:3","short":"Ac 1:3","text":"He presented himself alive to them after his suffering by many proofs, appearing to them during forty days and speaking about the kingdom of God.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 1:4","short":"Ac 1:4","text":"And while staying with them he ordered them not to depart from Jerusalem, but to wait for the promise of the Father, which, he said, \u201cyou heard from me;","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 1:5","short":"Ac 1:5","text":"for John baptized with water, but you will be baptized with the Holy Spirit not many days from now.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 1:6","short":"Ac 1:6","text":"So when they had come together, they asked him, \u201cLord, will you at this time restore the kingdom to Israel?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 1:7","short":"Ac 1:7","text":"He said to them, \u201cIt is not for you to know times or seasons that the Father has fixed by his own authority.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 1:8","short":"Ac 1:8","text":"But you will receive power when the Holy Spirit has come upon you, and you will be my witnesses in Jerusalem and in all Judea and Samaria, and to the end of the earth.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 1:9","short":"Ac 1:9","text":"And when he had said these things, as they were looking on, he was lifted up, and a cloud took him out of their sight.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 1:10","short":"Ac 1:10","text":"And while they were gazing into heaven as he went, behold, two men stood by them in white robes,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 1:11","short":"Ac 1:11","text":"and said, \u201cMen of Galilee, why do you stand looking into heaven? This Jesus, who was taken up from you into heaven, will come in the same way as you saw him go into heaven.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 1:12","short":"Ac 1:12","text":"Then they returned to Jerusalem from the mount called Olivet, which is near Jerusalem, a Sabbath day\u2019s journey away.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 1:13","short":"Ac 1:13","text":"And when they had entered, they went up to the upper room, where they were staying, Peter and John and James and Andrew, Philip and Thomas, Bartholomew and Matthew, James the son of Alphaeus and Simon the Zealot and Judas the son of James.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 1:14","short":"Ac 1:14","text":"All these with one accord were devoting themselves to prayer, together with the women and Mary the mother of Jesus, and his brothers.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 1:15","short":"Ac 1:15","text":"In those days Peter stood up among the brothers (the company of persons was in all about 120) and said,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 1:16","short":"Ac 1:16","text":"\u201cBrothers, the Scripture had to be fulfilled, which the Holy Spirit spoke beforehand by the mouth of David concerning Judas, who became a guide to those who arrested Jesus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 1:17","short":"Ac 1:17","text":"For he was numbered among us and was allotted his share in this ministry.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 1:18","short":"Ac 1:18","text":"(Now this man acquired a field with the reward of his wickedness, and falling headlong he burst open in the middle and all his bowels gushed out.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 1:19","short":"Ac 1:19","text":"And it became known to all the inhabitants of Jerusalem, so that the field was called in their own language Akeldama, that is, Field of Blood.)","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 1:20","short":"Ac 1:20","text":"\u201cFor it is written in the Book of Psalms, \u201c\u2018May his camp become desolate, and let there be no one to dwell in it\u2019; and \u201c\u2018Let another take his office.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 1:21","short":"Ac 1:21","text":"So one of the men who have accompanied us during all the time that the Lord Jesus went in and out among us,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 1:22","short":"Ac 1:22","text":"beginning from the baptism of John until the day when he was taken up from us\u2014one of these men must become with us a witness to his resurrection.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 1:23","short":"Ac 1:23","text":"And they put forward two, Joseph called Barsabbas, who was also called Justus, and Matthias.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 1:24","short":"Ac 1:24","text":"And they prayed and said, \u201cYou, Lord, who know the hearts of all, show which one of these two you have chosen","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 1:25","short":"Ac 1:25","text":"to take the place in this ministry and apostleship from which Judas turned aside to go to his own place.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 1:26","short":"Ac 1:26","text":"And they cast lots for them, and the lot fell on Matthias, and he was numbered with the eleven apostles.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_1.html","book":"Acts","ch":1,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 2:1","short":"Ac 2:1","text":"When the day of Pentecost arrived, they were all together in one place.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 2:2","short":"Ac 2:2","text":"And suddenly there came from heaven a sound like a mighty rushing wind, and it filled the entire house where they were sitting.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 2:3","short":"Ac 2:3","text":"And divided tongues as of fire appeared to them and rested on each one of them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 2:4","short":"Ac 2:4","text":"And they were all filled with the Holy Spirit and began to speak in other tongues as the Spirit gave them utterance.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 2:5","short":"Ac 2:5","text":"Now there were dwelling in Jerusalem Jews, devout men from every nation under heaven.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 2:6","short":"Ac 2:6","text":"And at this sound the multitude came together, and they were bewildered, because each one was hearing them speak in his own language.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 2:7","short":"Ac 2:7","text":"And they were amazed and astonished, saying, \u201cAre not all these who are speaking Galileans?","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 2:8","short":"Ac 2:8","text":"And how is it that we hear, each of us in his own native language?","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 2:9","short":"Ac 2:9","text":"Parthians and Medes and Elamites and residents of Mesopotamia, Judea and Cappadocia, Pontus and Asia,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 2:10","short":"Ac 2:10","text":"Phrygia and Pamphylia, Egypt and the parts of Libya belonging to Cyrene, and visitors from Rome,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 2:11","short":"Ac 2:11","text":"both Jews and proselytes, Cretans and Arabians\u2014we hear them telling in our own tongues the mighty works of God.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 2:12","short":"Ac 2:12","text":"And all were amazed and perplexed, saying to one another, \u201cWhat does this mean?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 2:13","short":"Ac 2:13","text":"But others mocking said, \u201cThey are filled with new wine.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 2:14","short":"Ac 2:14","text":"But Peter, standing with the eleven, lifted up his voice and addressed them: \u201cMen of Judea and all who dwell in Jerusalem, let this be known to you, and give ear to my words.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 2:15","short":"Ac 2:15","text":"For these people are not drunk, as you suppose, since it is only the third hour of the day.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 2:16","short":"Ac 2:16","text":"But this is what was uttered through the prophet Joel:","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 2:17","short":"Ac 2:17","text":"\u201c\u2018And in the last days it shall be, God declares, that I will pour out my Spirit on all flesh, and your sons and your daughters shall prophesy, and your young men shall see visions, and your old men shall dream dreams;","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 2:18","short":"Ac 2:18","text":"even on my male servants and female servants in those days I will pour out my Spirit, and they shall prophesy.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 2:19","short":"Ac 2:19","text":"And I will show wonders in the heavens above and signs on the earth below, blood, and fire, and vapor of smoke;","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 2:20","short":"Ac 2:20","text":"the sun shall be turned to darkness and the moon to blood, before the day of the Lord comes, the great and magnificent day.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 2:21","short":"Ac 2:21","text":"And it shall come to pass that everyone who calls upon the name of the Lord shall be saved.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 2:22","short":"Ac 2:22","text":"\u201cMen of Israel, hear these words: Jesus of Nazareth, a man attested to you by God with mighty works and wonders and signs that God did through him in your midst, as you yourselves know\u2014","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 2:23","short":"Ac 2:23","text":"this Jesus, delivered up according to the definite plan and foreknowledge of God, you crucified and killed by the hands of lawless men.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 2:24","short":"Ac 2:24","text":"God raised him up, loosing the pangs of death, because it was not possible for him to be held by it.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 2:25","short":"Ac 2:25","text":"For David says concerning him, \u201c\u2018I saw the Lord always before me, for he is at my right hand that I may not be shaken;","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 2:26","short":"Ac 2:26","text":"therefore my heart was glad, and my tongue rejoiced; my flesh also will dwell in hope.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 2:27","short":"Ac 2:27","text":"For you will not abandon my soul to Hades, or let your Holy One see corruption.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 2:28","short":"Ac 2:28","text":"You have made known to me the paths of life; you will make me full of gladness with your presence.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 2:29","short":"Ac 2:29","text":"\u201cBrothers, I may say to you with confidence about the patriarch David that he both died and was buried, and his tomb is with us to this day.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":29},{"ref":"Acts 2:30","short":"Ac 2:30","text":"Being therefore a prophet, and knowing that God had sworn with an oath to him that he would set one of his descendants on his throne,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":30},{"ref":"Acts 2:31","short":"Ac 2:31","text":"he foresaw and spoke about the resurrection of the Christ, that he was not abandoned to Hades, nor did his flesh see corruption.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":31},{"ref":"Acts 2:32","short":"Ac 2:32","text":"This Jesus God raised up, and of that we all are witnesses.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":32},{"ref":"Acts 2:33","short":"Ac 2:33","text":"Being therefore exalted at the right hand of God, and having received from the Father the promise of the Holy Spirit, he has poured out this that you yourselves are seeing and hearing.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":33},{"ref":"Acts 2:34","short":"Ac 2:34","text":"For David did not ascend into the heavens, but he himself says, \u201c\u2018The Lord said to my Lord, \u201cSit at my right hand,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":34},{"ref":"Acts 2:35","short":"Ac 2:35","text":"until I make your enemies your footstool.\u201d\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":35},{"ref":"Acts 2:36","short":"Ac 2:36","text":"Let all the house of Israel therefore know for certain that God has made him both Lord and Christ, this Jesus whom you crucified.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":36},{"ref":"Acts 2:37","short":"Ac 2:37","text":"Now when they heard this they were cut to the heart, and said to Peter and the rest of the apostles, \u201cBrothers, what shall we do?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":37},{"ref":"Acts 2:38","short":"Ac 2:38","text":"And Peter said to them, \u201cRepent and be baptized every one of you in the name of Jesus Christ for the forgiveness of your sins, and you will receive the gift of the Holy Spirit.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":38},{"ref":"Acts 2:39","short":"Ac 2:39","text":"For the promise is for you and for your children and for all who are far off, everyone whom the Lord our God calls to himself.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":39},{"ref":"Acts 2:40","short":"Ac 2:40","text":"And with many other words he bore witness and continued to exhort them, saying, \u201cSave yourselves from this crooked generation.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":40},{"ref":"Acts 2:41","short":"Ac 2:41","text":"So those who received his word were baptized, and there were added that day about three thousand souls.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":41},{"ref":"Acts 2:42","short":"Ac 2:42","text":"And they devoted themselves to the apostles\u2019 teaching and the fellowship, to the breaking of bread and the prayers.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":42},{"ref":"Acts 2:43","short":"Ac 2:43","text":"And awe came upon every soul, and many wonders and signs were being done through the apostles.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":43},{"ref":"Acts 2:44","short":"Ac 2:44","text":"And all who believed were together and had all things in common.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":44},{"ref":"Acts 2:45","short":"Ac 2:45","text":"And they were selling their possessions and belongings and distributing the proceeds to all, as any had need.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":45},{"ref":"Acts 2:46","short":"Ac 2:46","text":"And day by day, attending the temple together and breaking bread in their homes, they received their food with glad and generous hearts,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":46},{"ref":"Acts 2:47","short":"Ac 2:47","text":"praising God and having favor with all the people. And the Lord added to their number day by day those who were being saved.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_2.html","book":"Acts","ch":2,"v":47},{"ref":"Acts 3:1","short":"Ac 3:1","text":"Now Peter and John were going up to the temple at the hour of prayer, the ninth hour.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 3:2","short":"Ac 3:2","text":"And a man lame from birth was being carried, whom they laid daily at the gate of the temple that is called the Beautiful Gate to ask alms of those entering the temple.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 3:3","short":"Ac 3:3","text":"Seeing Peter and John about to go into the temple, he asked to receive alms.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 3:4","short":"Ac 3:4","text":"And Peter directed his gaze at him, as did John, and said, \u201cLook at us.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 3:5","short":"Ac 3:5","text":"And he fixed his attention on them, expecting to receive something from them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 3:6","short":"Ac 3:6","text":"But Peter said, \u201cI have no silver and gold, but what I do have I give to you. In the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, rise up and walk!\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 3:7","short":"Ac 3:7","text":"And he took him by the right hand and raised him up, and immediately his feet and ankles were made strong.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 3:8","short":"Ac 3:8","text":"And leaping up, he stood and began to walk, and entered the temple with them, walking and leaping and praising God.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 3:9","short":"Ac 3:9","text":"And all the people saw him walking and praising God,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 3:10","short":"Ac 3:10","text":"and recognized him as the one who sat at the Beautiful Gate of the temple, asking for alms. And they were filled with wonder and amazement at what had happened to him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 3:11","short":"Ac 3:11","text":"While he clung to Peter and John, all the people, utterly astounded, ran together to them in the portico called Solomon\u2019s.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 3:12","short":"Ac 3:12","text":"And when Peter saw it he addressed the people: \u201cMen of Israel, why do you wonder at this, or why do you stare at us, as though by our own power or piety we have made him walk?","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 3:13","short":"Ac 3:13","text":"The God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob, the God of our fathers, glorified his servant Jesus, whom you delivered over and denied in the presence of Pilate, when he had decided to release him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 3:14","short":"Ac 3:14","text":"But you denied the Holy and Righteous One, and asked for a murderer to be granted to you,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 3:15","short":"Ac 3:15","text":"and you killed the Author of life, whom God raised from the dead. To this we are witnesses.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 3:16","short":"Ac 3:16","text":"And his name\u2014by faith in his name\u2014has made this man strong whom you see and know, and the faith that is through Jesus has given the man this perfect health in the presence of you all.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 3:17","short":"Ac 3:17","text":"\u201cAnd now, brothers, I know that you acted in ignorance, as did also your rulers.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 3:18","short":"Ac 3:18","text":"But what God foretold by the mouth of all the prophets, that his Christ would suffer, he thus fulfilled.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 3:19","short":"Ac 3:19","text":"Repent therefore, and turn back, that your sins may be blotted out,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 3:20","short":"Ac 3:20","text":"that times of refreshing may come from the presence of the Lord, and that he may send the Christ appointed for you, Jesus,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 3:21","short":"Ac 3:21","text":"whom heaven must receive until the time for restoring all the things about which God spoke by the mouth of his holy prophets long ago.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 3:22","short":"Ac 3:22","text":"Moses said, \u2018The Lord God will raise up for you a prophet like me from your brothers. You shall listen to him in whatever he tells you.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 3:23","short":"Ac 3:23","text":"And it shall be that every soul who does not listen to that prophet shall be destroyed from the people.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 3:24","short":"Ac 3:24","text":"And all the prophets who have spoken, from Samuel and those who came after him, also proclaimed these days.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 3:25","short":"Ac 3:25","text":"You are the sons of the prophets and of the covenant that God made with your fathers, saying to Abraham, \u2018And in your offspring shall all the families of the earth be blessed.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 3:26","short":"Ac 3:26","text":"God, having raised up his servant, sent him to you first, to bless you by turning every one of you from your wickedness.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_3.html","book":"Acts","ch":3,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 4:1","short":"Ac 4:1","text":"And as they were speaking to the people, the priests and the captain of the temple and the Sadducees came upon them,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 4:2","short":"Ac 4:2","text":"greatly annoyed because they were teaching the people and proclaiming in Jesus the resurrection from the dead.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 4:3","short":"Ac 4:3","text":"And they arrested them and put them in custody until the next day, for it was already evening.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 4:4","short":"Ac 4:4","text":"But many of those who had heard the word believed, and the number of the men came to about five thousand.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 4:5","short":"Ac 4:5","text":"On the next day their rulers and elders and scribes gathered together in Jerusalem,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 4:6","short":"Ac 4:6","text":"with Annas the high priest and Caiaphas and John and Alexander, and all who were of the high-priestly family.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 4:7","short":"Ac 4:7","text":"And when they had set them in the midst, they inquired, \u201cBy what power or by what name did you do this?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 4:8","short":"Ac 4:8","text":"Then Peter, filled with the Holy Spirit, said to them, \u201cRulers of the people and elders,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 4:9","short":"Ac 4:9","text":"if we are being examined today concerning a good deed done to a crippled man, by what means this man has been healed,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 4:10","short":"Ac 4:10","text":"let it be known to all of you and to all the people of Israel that by the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, whom you crucified, whom God raised from the dead\u2014by him this man is standing before you well.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 4:11","short":"Ac 4:11","text":"This Jesus is the stone that was rejected by you, the builders, which has become the cornerstone.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 4:12","short":"Ac 4:12","text":"And there is salvation in no one else, for there is no other name under heaven given among men by which we must be saved.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 4:13","short":"Ac 4:13","text":"Now when they saw the boldness of Peter and John, and perceived that they were uneducated, common men, they were astonished. And they recognized that they had been with Jesus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 4:14","short":"Ac 4:14","text":"But seeing the man who was healed standing beside them, they had nothing to say in opposition.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 4:15","short":"Ac 4:15","text":"But when they had commanded them to leave the council, they conferred with one another,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 4:16","short":"Ac 4:16","text":"saying, \u201cWhat shall we do with these men? For that a notable sign has been performed through them is evident to all the inhabitants of Jerusalem, and we cannot deny it.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 4:17","short":"Ac 4:17","text":"But in order that it may spread no further among the people, let us warn them to speak no more to anyone in this name.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 4:18","short":"Ac 4:18","text":"So they called them and charged them not to speak or teach at all in the name of Jesus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 4:19","short":"Ac 4:19","text":"But Peter and John answered them, \u201cWhether it is right in the sight of God to listen to you rather than to God, you must judge,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 4:20","short":"Ac 4:20","text":"for we cannot but speak of what we have seen and heard.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 4:21","short":"Ac 4:21","text":"And when they had further threatened them, they let them go, finding no way to punish them, because of the people, for all were praising God for what had happened.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 4:22","short":"Ac 4:22","text":"For the man on whom this sign of healing was performed was more than forty years old.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 4:23","short":"Ac 4:23","text":"When they were released, they went to their friends and reported what the chief priests and the elders had said to them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 4:24","short":"Ac 4:24","text":"And when they heard it, they lifted their voices together to God and said, \u201cSovereign Lord, who made the heaven and the earth and the sea and everything in them,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 4:25","short":"Ac 4:25","text":"who through the mouth of our father David, your servant, said by the Holy Spirit, \u201c\u2018Why did the Gentiles rage, and the peoples plot in vain?","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 4:26","short":"Ac 4:26","text":"The kings of the earth set themselves, and the rulers were gathered together, against the Lord and against his Anointed\u2019\u2014","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 4:27","short":"Ac 4:27","text":"for truly in this city there were gathered together against your holy servant Jesus, whom you anointed, both Herod and Pontius Pilate, along with the Gentiles and the peoples of Israel,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 4:28","short":"Ac 4:28","text":"to do whatever your hand and your plan had predestined to take place.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 4:29","short":"Ac 4:29","text":"And now, Lord, look upon their threats and grant to your servants to continue to speak your word with all boldness,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":29},{"ref":"Acts 4:30","short":"Ac 4:30","text":"while you stretch out your hand to heal, and signs and wonders are performed through the name of your holy servant Jesus.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":30},{"ref":"Acts 4:31","short":"Ac 4:31","text":"And when they had prayed, the place in which they were gathered together was shaken, and they were all filled with the Holy Spirit and continued to speak the word of God with boldness.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":31},{"ref":"Acts 4:32","short":"Ac 4:32","text":"Now the full number of those who believed were of one heart and soul, and no one said that any of the things that belonged to him was his own, but they had everything in common.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":32},{"ref":"Acts 4:33","short":"Ac 4:33","text":"And with great power the apostles were giving their testimony to the resurrection of the Lord Jesus, and great grace was upon them all.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":33},{"ref":"Acts 4:34","short":"Ac 4:34","text":"There was not a needy person among them, for as many as were owners of lands or houses sold them and brought the proceeds of what was sold","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":34},{"ref":"Acts 4:35","short":"Ac 4:35","text":"and laid it at the apostles\u2019 feet, and it was distributed to each as any had need.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":35},{"ref":"Acts 4:36","short":"Ac 4:36","text":"Thus Joseph, who was also called by the apostles Barnabas (which means son of encouragement), a Levite, a native of Cyprus,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":36},{"ref":"Acts 4:37","short":"Ac 4:37","text":"sold a field that belonged to him and brought the money and laid it at the apostles\u2019 feet.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_4.html","book":"Acts","ch":4,"v":37},{"ref":"Acts 5:1","short":"Ac 5:1","text":"But a man named Ananias, with his wife Sapphira, sold a piece of property,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 5:2","short":"Ac 5:2","text":"and with his wife\u2019s knowledge he kept back for himself some of the proceeds and brought only a part of it and laid it at the apostles\u2019 feet.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 5:3","short":"Ac 5:3","text":"But Peter said, \u201cAnanias, why has Satan filled your heart to lie to the Holy Spirit and to keep back for yourself part of the proceeds of the land?","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 5:4","short":"Ac 5:4","text":"While it remained unsold, did it not remain your own? And after it was sold, was it not at your disposal? Why is it that you have contrived this deed in your heart? You have not lied to man but to God.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 5:5","short":"Ac 5:5","text":"When Ananias heard these words, he fell down and breathed his last. And great fear came upon all who heard of it.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 5:6","short":"Ac 5:6","text":"The young men rose and wrapped him up and carried him out and buried him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 5:7","short":"Ac 5:7","text":"After an interval of about three hours his wife came in, not knowing what had happened.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 5:8","short":"Ac 5:8","text":"And Peter said to her, \u201cTell me whether you sold the land for so much.\u201d And she said, \u201cYes, for so much.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 5:9","short":"Ac 5:9","text":"But Peter said to her, \u201cHow is it that you have agreed together to test the Spirit of the Lord? Behold, the feet of those who have buried your husband are at the door, and they will carry you out.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 5:10","short":"Ac 5:10","text":"Immediately she fell down at his feet and breathed her last. When the young men came in they found her dead, and they carried her out and buried her beside her husband.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 5:11","short":"Ac 5:11","text":"And great fear came upon the whole church and upon all who heard of these things.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 5:12","short":"Ac 5:12","text":"Now many signs and wonders were regularly done among the people by the hands of the apostles. And they were all together in Solomon\u2019s Portico.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 5:13","short":"Ac 5:13","text":"None of the rest dared join them, but the people held them in high esteem.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 5:14","short":"Ac 5:14","text":"And more than ever believers were added to the Lord, multitudes of both men and women,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 5:15","short":"Ac 5:15","text":"so that they even carried out the sick into the streets and laid them on cots and mats, that as Peter came by at least his shadow might fall on some of them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 5:16","short":"Ac 5:16","text":"The people also gathered from the towns around Jerusalem, bringing the sick and those afflicted with unclean spirits, and they were all healed.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 5:17","short":"Ac 5:17","text":"But the high priest rose up, and all who were with him (that is, the party of the Sadducees), and filled with jealousy","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 5:18","short":"Ac 5:18","text":"they arrested the apostles and put them in the public prison.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 5:19","short":"Ac 5:19","text":"But during the night an angel of the Lord opened the prison doors and brought them out, and said,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 5:20","short":"Ac 5:20","text":"\u201cGo and stand in the temple and speak to the people all the words of this Life.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 5:21","short":"Ac 5:21","text":"And when they heard this, they entered the temple at daybreak and began to teach. Now when the high priest came, and those who were with him, they called together the council, all the senate of the people of Israel, and sent to the prison to have them brought.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 5:22","short":"Ac 5:22","text":"But when the officers came, they did not find them in the prison, so they returned and reported,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 5:23","short":"Ac 5:23","text":"\u201cWe found the prison securely locked and the guards standing at the doors, but when we opened them we found no one inside.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 5:24","short":"Ac 5:24","text":"Now when the captain of the temple and the chief priests heard these words, they were greatly perplexed about them, wondering what this would come to.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 5:25","short":"Ac 5:25","text":"And someone came and told them, \u201cLook! The men whom you put in prison are standing in the temple and teaching the people.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 5:26","short":"Ac 5:26","text":"Then the captain with the officers went and brought them, but not by force, for they were afraid of being stoned by the people.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 5:27","short":"Ac 5:27","text":"And when they had brought them, they set them before the council. And the high priest questioned them,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 5:28","short":"Ac 5:28","text":"saying, \u201cWe strictly charged you not to teach in this name, yet here you have filled Jerusalem with your teaching, and you intend to bring this man\u2019s blood upon us.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 5:29","short":"Ac 5:29","text":"But Peter and the apostles answered, \u201cWe must obey God rather than men.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":29},{"ref":"Acts 5:30","short":"Ac 5:30","text":"The God of our fathers raised Jesus, whom you killed by hanging him on a tree.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":30},{"ref":"Acts 5:31","short":"Ac 5:31","text":"God exalted him at his right hand as Leader and Savior, to give repentance to Israel and forgiveness of sins.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":31},{"ref":"Acts 5:32","short":"Ac 5:32","text":"And we are witnesses to these things, and so is the Holy Spirit, whom God has given to those who obey him.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":32},{"ref":"Acts 5:33","short":"Ac 5:33","text":"When they heard this, they were enraged and wanted to kill them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":33},{"ref":"Acts 5:34","short":"Ac 5:34","text":"But a Pharisee in the council named Gamaliel, a teacher of the law held in honor by all the people, stood up and gave orders to put the men outside for a little while.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":34},{"ref":"Acts 5:35","short":"Ac 5:35","text":"And he said to them, \u201cMen of Israel, take care what you are about to do with these men.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":35},{"ref":"Acts 5:36","short":"Ac 5:36","text":"For before these days Theudas rose up, claiming to be somebody, and a number of men, about four hundred, joined him. He was killed, and all who followed him were dispersed and came to nothing.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":36},{"ref":"Acts 5:37","short":"Ac 5:37","text":"After him Judas the Galilean rose up in the days of the census and drew away some of the people after him. He too perished, and all who followed him were scattered.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":37},{"ref":"Acts 5:38","short":"Ac 5:38","text":"So in the present case I tell you, keep away from these men and let them alone, for if this plan or this undertaking is of man, it will fail;","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":38},{"ref":"Acts 5:39","short":"Ac 5:39","text":"but if it is of God, you will not be able to overthrow them. You might even be found opposing God!\u201d So they took his advice,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":39},{"ref":"Acts 5:40","short":"Ac 5:40","text":"and when they had called in the apostles, they beat them and charged them not to speak in the name of Jesus, and let them go.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":40},{"ref":"Acts 5:41","short":"Ac 5:41","text":"Then they left the presence of the council, rejoicing that they were counted worthy to suffer dishonor for the name.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":41},{"ref":"Acts 5:42","short":"Ac 5:42","text":"And every day, in the temple and from house to house, they did not cease teaching and preaching that the Christ is Jesus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_5.html","book":"Acts","ch":5,"v":42},{"ref":"Acts 6:1","short":"Ac 6:1","text":"Now in these days when the disciples were increasing in number, a complaint by the Hellenists arose against the Hebrews because their widows were being neglected in the daily distribution.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_6.html","book":"Acts","ch":6,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 6:2","short":"Ac 6:2","text":"And the twelve summoned the full number of the disciples and said, \u201cIt is not right that we should give up preaching the word of God to serve tables.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_6.html","book":"Acts","ch":6,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 6:3","short":"Ac 6:3","text":"Therefore, brothers, pick out from among you seven men of good repute, full of the Spirit and of wisdom, whom we will appoint to this duty.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_6.html","book":"Acts","ch":6,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 6:4","short":"Ac 6:4","text":"But we will devote ourselves to prayer and to the ministry of the word.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_6.html","book":"Acts","ch":6,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 6:5","short":"Ac 6:5","text":"And what they said pleased the whole gathering, and they chose Stephen, a man full of faith and of the Holy Spirit, and Philip, and Prochorus, and Nicanor, and Timon, and Parmenas, and Nicolaus, a proselyte of Antioch.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_6.html","book":"Acts","ch":6,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 6:6","short":"Ac 6:6","text":"These they set before the apostles, and they prayed and laid their hands on them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_6.html","book":"Acts","ch":6,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 6:7","short":"Ac 6:7","text":"And the word of God continued to increase, and the number of the disciples multiplied greatly in Jerusalem, and a great many of the priests became obedient to the faith.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_6.html","book":"Acts","ch":6,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 6:8","short":"Ac 6:8","text":"And Stephen, full of grace and power, was doing great wonders and signs among the people.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_6.html","book":"Acts","ch":6,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 6:9","short":"Ac 6:9","text":"Then some of those who belonged to the synagogue of the Freedmen (as it was called), and of the Cyrenians, and of the Alexandrians, and of those from Cilicia and Asia, rose up and disputed with Stephen.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_6.html","book":"Acts","ch":6,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 6:10","short":"Ac 6:10","text":"But they could not withstand the wisdom and the Spirit with which he was speaking.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_6.html","book":"Acts","ch":6,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 6:11","short":"Ac 6:11","text":"Then they secretly instigated men who said, \u201cWe have heard him speak blasphemous words against Moses and God.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_6.html","book":"Acts","ch":6,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 6:12","short":"Ac 6:12","text":"And they stirred up the people and the elders and the scribes, and they came upon him and seized him and brought him before the council,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_6.html","book":"Acts","ch":6,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 6:13","short":"Ac 6:13","text":"and they set up false witnesses who said, \u201cThis man never ceases to speak words against this holy place and the law,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_6.html","book":"Acts","ch":6,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 6:14","short":"Ac 6:14","text":"for we have heard him say that this Jesus of Nazareth will destroy this place and will change the customs that Moses delivered to us.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_6.html","book":"Acts","ch":6,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 6:15","short":"Ac 6:15","text":"And gazing at him, all who sat in the council saw that his face was like the face of an angel.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_6.html","book":"Acts","ch":6,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 7:1","short":"Ac 7:1","text":"And the high priest said, \u201cAre these things so?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 7:2","short":"Ac 7:2","text":"And Stephen said: \u201cBrothers and fathers, hear me. The God of glory appeared to our father Abraham when he was in Mesopotamia, before he lived in Haran,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 7:3","short":"Ac 7:3","text":"and said to him, \u2018Go out from your land and from your kindred and go into the land that I will show you.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 7:4","short":"Ac 7:4","text":"Then he went out from the land of the Chaldeans and lived in Haran. And after his father died, God removed him from there into this land in which you are now living.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 7:5","short":"Ac 7:5","text":"Yet he gave him no inheritance in it, not even a foot\u2019s length, but promised to give it to him as a possession and to his offspring after him, though he had no child.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 7:6","short":"Ac 7:6","text":"And God spoke to this effect\u2014that his offspring would be sojourners in a land belonging to others, who would enslave them and afflict them four hundred years.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 7:7","short":"Ac 7:7","text":"\u2018But I will judge the nation that they serve,\u2019 said God, \u2018and after that they shall come out and worship me in this place.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 7:8","short":"Ac 7:8","text":"And he gave him the covenant of circumcision. And so Abraham became the father of Isaac, and circumcised him on the eighth day, and Isaac became the father of Jacob, and Jacob of the twelve patriarchs.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 7:9","short":"Ac 7:9","text":"\u201cAnd the patriarchs, jealous of Joseph, sold him into Egypt; but God was with him","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 7:10","short":"Ac 7:10","text":"and rescued him out of all his afflictions and gave him favor and wisdom before Pharaoh, king of Egypt, who made him ruler over Egypt and over all his household.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 7:11","short":"Ac 7:11","text":"Now there came a famine throughout all Egypt and Canaan, and great affliction, and our fathers could find no food.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 7:12","short":"Ac 7:12","text":"But when Jacob heard that there was grain in Egypt, he sent out our fathers on their first visit.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 7:13","short":"Ac 7:13","text":"And on the second visit Joseph made himself known to his brothers, and Joseph\u2019s family became known to Pharaoh.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 7:14","short":"Ac 7:14","text":"And Joseph sent and summoned Jacob his father and all his kindred, seventy-five persons in all.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 7:15","short":"Ac 7:15","text":"And Jacob went down into Egypt, and he died, he and our fathers,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 7:16","short":"Ac 7:16","text":"and they were carried back to Shechem and laid in the tomb that Abraham had bought for a sum of silver from the sons of Hamor in Shechem.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 7:17","short":"Ac 7:17","text":"\u201cBut as the time of the promise drew near, which God had granted to Abraham, the people increased and multiplied in Egypt","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 7:18","short":"Ac 7:18","text":"until there arose over Egypt another king who did not know Joseph.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 7:19","short":"Ac 7:19","text":"He dealt shrewdly with our race and forced our fathers to expose their infants, so that they would not be kept alive.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 7:20","short":"Ac 7:20","text":"At this time Moses was born; and he was beautiful in God\u2019s sight. And he was brought up for three months in his father\u2019s house,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 7:21","short":"Ac 7:21","text":"and when he was exposed, Pharaoh\u2019s daughter adopted him and brought him up as her own son.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 7:22","short":"Ac 7:22","text":"And Moses was instructed in all the wisdom of the Egyptians, and he was mighty in his words and deeds.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 7:23","short":"Ac 7:23","text":"\u201cWhen he was forty years old, it came into his heart to visit his brothers, the children of Israel.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 7:24","short":"Ac 7:24","text":"And seeing one of them being wronged, he defended the oppressed man and avenged him by striking down the Egyptian.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 7:25","short":"Ac 7:25","text":"He supposed that his brothers would understand that God was giving them salvation by his hand, but they did not understand.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 7:26","short":"Ac 7:26","text":"And on the following day he appeared to them as they were quarreling and tried to reconcile them, saying, \u2018Men, you are brothers. Why do you wrong each other?\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 7:27","short":"Ac 7:27","text":"But the man who was wronging his neighbor thrust him aside, saying, \u2018Who made you a ruler and a judge over us?","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 7:28","short":"Ac 7:28","text":"Do you want to kill me as you killed the Egyptian yesterday?\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 7:29","short":"Ac 7:29","text":"At this retort Moses fled and became an exile in the land of Midian, where he became the father of two sons.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":29},{"ref":"Acts 7:30","short":"Ac 7:30","text":"\u201cNow when forty years had passed, an angel appeared to him in the wilderness of Mount Sinai, in a flame of fire in a bush.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":30},{"ref":"Acts 7:31","short":"Ac 7:31","text":"When Moses saw it, he was amazed at the sight, and as he drew near to look, there came the voice of the Lord:","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":31},{"ref":"Acts 7:32","short":"Ac 7:32","text":"\u2018I am the God of your fathers, the God of Abraham and of Isaac and of Jacob.\u2019 And Moses trembled and did not dare to look.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":32},{"ref":"Acts 7:33","short":"Ac 7:33","text":"Then the Lord said to him, \u2018Take off the sandals from your feet, for the place where you are standing is holy ground.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":33},{"ref":"Acts 7:34","short":"Ac 7:34","text":"I have surely seen the affliction of my people who are in Egypt, and have heard their groaning, and I have come down to deliver them. And now come, I will send you to Egypt.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":34},{"ref":"Acts 7:35","short":"Ac 7:35","text":"\u201cThis Moses, whom they rejected, saying, \u2018Who made you a ruler and a judge?\u2019\u2014this man God sent as both ruler and redeemer by the hand of the angel who appeared to him in the bush.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":35},{"ref":"Acts 7:36","short":"Ac 7:36","text":"This man led them out, performing wonders and signs in Egypt and at the Red Sea and in the wilderness for forty years.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":36},{"ref":"Acts 7:37","short":"Ac 7:37","text":"This is the Moses who said to the Israelites, \u2018God will raise up for you a prophet like me from your brothers.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":37},{"ref":"Acts 7:38","short":"Ac 7:38","text":"This is the one who was in the congregation in the wilderness with the angel who spoke to him at Mount Sinai, and with our fathers. He received living oracles to give to us.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":38},{"ref":"Acts 7:39","short":"Ac 7:39","text":"Our fathers refused to obey him, but thrust him aside, and in their hearts they turned to Egypt,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":39},{"ref":"Acts 7:40","short":"Ac 7:40","text":"saying to Aaron, \u2018Make for us gods who will go before us. As for this Moses who led us out from the land of Egypt, we do not know what has become of him.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":40},{"ref":"Acts 7:41","short":"Ac 7:41","text":"And they made a calf in those days, and offered a sacrifice to the idol and were rejoicing in the works of their hands.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":41},{"ref":"Acts 7:42","short":"Ac 7:42","text":"But God turned away and gave them over to worship the host of heaven, as it is written in the book of the prophets: \u201c\u2018Did you bring to me slain beasts and sacrifices, during the forty years in the wilderness, O house of Israel?","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":42},{"ref":"Acts 7:43","short":"Ac 7:43","text":"You took up the tent of Moloch and the star of your god Rephan, the images that you made to worship; and I will send you into exile beyond Babylon.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":43},{"ref":"Acts 7:44","short":"Ac 7:44","text":"\u201cOur fathers had the tent of witness in the wilderness, just as he who spoke to Moses directed him to make it, according to the pattern that he had seen.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":44},{"ref":"Acts 7:45","short":"Ac 7:45","text":"Our fathers in turn brought it in with Joshua when they dispossessed the nations that God drove out before our fathers. So it was until the days of David,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":45},{"ref":"Acts 7:46","short":"Ac 7:46","text":"who found favor in the sight of God and asked to find a dwelling place for the God of Jacob.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":46},{"ref":"Acts 7:47","short":"Ac 7:47","text":"But it was Solomon who built a house for him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":47},{"ref":"Acts 7:48","short":"Ac 7:48","text":"Yet the Most High does not dwell in houses made by hands, as the prophet says,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":48},{"ref":"Acts 7:49","short":"Ac 7:49","text":"\u201c\u2018Heaven is my throne, and the earth is my footstool. What kind of house will you build for me, says the Lord, or what is the place of my rest?","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":49},{"ref":"Acts 7:50","short":"Ac 7:50","text":"Did not my hand make all these things?\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":50},{"ref":"Acts 7:51","short":"Ac 7:51","text":"\u201cYou stiff-necked people, uncircumcised in heart and ears, you always resist the Holy Spirit. As your fathers did, so do you.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":51},{"ref":"Acts 7:52","short":"Ac 7:52","text":"Which of the prophets did your fathers not persecute? And they killed those who announced beforehand the coming of the Righteous One, whom you have now betrayed and murdered,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":52},{"ref":"Acts 7:53","short":"Ac 7:53","text":"you who received the law as delivered by angels and did not keep it.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":53},{"ref":"Acts 7:54","short":"Ac 7:54","text":"Now when they heard these things they were enraged, and they ground their teeth at him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":54},{"ref":"Acts 7:55","short":"Ac 7:55","text":"But he, full of the Holy Spirit, gazed into heaven and saw the glory of God, and Jesus standing at the right hand of God.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":55},{"ref":"Acts 7:56","short":"Ac 7:56","text":"And he said, \u201cBehold, I see the heavens opened, and the Son of Man standing at the right hand of God.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":56},{"ref":"Acts 7:57","short":"Ac 7:57","text":"But they cried out with a loud voice and stopped their ears and rushed together at him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":57},{"ref":"Acts 7:58","short":"Ac 7:58","text":"Then they cast him out of the city and stoned him. And the witnesses laid down their garments at the feet of a young man named Saul.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":58},{"ref":"Acts 7:59","short":"Ac 7:59","text":"And as they were stoning Stephen, he called out, \u201cLord Jesus, receive my spirit.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":59},{"ref":"Acts 7:60","short":"Ac 7:60","text":"And falling to his knees he cried out with a loud voice, \u201cLord, do not hold this sin against them.\u201d And when he had said this, he fell asleep.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_7.html","book":"Acts","ch":7,"v":60},{"ref":"Acts 8:1","short":"Ac 8:1","text":"And Saul approved of his execution. And there arose on that day a great persecution against the church in Jerusalem, and they were all scattered throughout the regions of Judea and Samaria, except the apostles.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 8:2","short":"Ac 8:2","text":"Devout men buried Stephen and made great lamentation over him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 8:3","short":"Ac 8:3","text":"But Saul was ravaging the church, and entering house after house, he dragged off men and women and committed them to prison.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 8:4","short":"Ac 8:4","text":"Now those who were scattered went about preaching the word.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 8:5","short":"Ac 8:5","text":"Philip went down to the city of Samaria and proclaimed to them the Christ.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 8:6","short":"Ac 8:6","text":"And the crowds with one accord paid attention to what was being said by Philip, when they heard him and saw the signs that he did.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 8:7","short":"Ac 8:7","text":"For unclean spirits, crying out with a loud voice, came out of many who had them, and many who were paralyzed or lame were healed.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 8:8","short":"Ac 8:8","text":"So there was much joy in that city.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 8:9","short":"Ac 8:9","text":"But there was a man named Simon, who had previously practiced magic in the city and amazed the people of Samaria, saying that he himself was somebody great.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 8:10","short":"Ac 8:10","text":"They all paid attention to him, from the least to the greatest, saying, \u201cThis man is the power of God that is called Great.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 8:11","short":"Ac 8:11","text":"And they paid attention to him because for a long time he had amazed them with his magic.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 8:12","short":"Ac 8:12","text":"But when they believed Philip as he preached good news about the kingdom of God and the name of Jesus Christ, they were baptized, both men and women.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 8:13","short":"Ac 8:13","text":"Even Simon himself believed, and after being baptized he continued with Philip. And seeing signs and great miracles performed, he was amazed.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 8:14","short":"Ac 8:14","text":"Now when the apostles at Jerusalem heard that Samaria had received the word of God, they sent to them Peter and John,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 8:15","short":"Ac 8:15","text":"who came down and prayed for them that they might receive the Holy Spirit,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 8:16","short":"Ac 8:16","text":"for he had not yet fallen on any of them, but they had only been baptized in the name of the Lord Jesus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 8:17","short":"Ac 8:17","text":"Then they laid their hands on them and they received the Holy Spirit.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 8:18","short":"Ac 8:18","text":"Now when Simon saw that the Spirit was given through the laying on of the apostles\u2019 hands, he offered them money,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 8:19","short":"Ac 8:19","text":"saying, \u201cGive me this power also, so that anyone on whom I lay my hands may receive the Holy Spirit.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 8:20","short":"Ac 8:20","text":"But Peter said to him, \u201cMay your silver perish with you, because you thought you could obtain the gift of God with money!","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 8:21","short":"Ac 8:21","text":"You have neither part nor lot in this matter, for your heart is not right before God.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 8:22","short":"Ac 8:22","text":"Repent, therefore, of this wickedness of yours, and pray to the Lord that, if possible, the intent of your heart may be forgiven you.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 8:23","short":"Ac 8:23","text":"For I see that you are in the gall of bitterness and in the bond of iniquity.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 8:24","short":"Ac 8:24","text":"And Simon answered, \u201cPray for me to the Lord, that nothing of what you have said may come upon me.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 8:25","short":"Ac 8:25","text":"Now when they had testified and spoken the word of the Lord, they returned to Jerusalem, preaching the gospel to many villages of the Samaritans.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 8:26","short":"Ac 8:26","text":"Now an angel of the Lord said to Philip, \u201cRise and go toward the south to the road that goes down from Jerusalem to Gaza.\u201d This is a desert place.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 8:27","short":"Ac 8:27","text":"And he rose and went. And there was an Ethiopian, a eunuch, a court official of Candace, queen of the Ethiopians, who was in charge of all her treasure. He had come to Jerusalem to worship","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 8:28","short":"Ac 8:28","text":"and was returning, seated in his chariot, and he was reading the prophet Isaiah.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 8:29","short":"Ac 8:29","text":"And the Spirit said to Philip, \u201cGo over and join this chariot.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":29},{"ref":"Acts 8:30","short":"Ac 8:30","text":"So Philip ran to him and heard him reading Isaiah the prophet and asked, \u201cDo you understand what you are reading?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":30},{"ref":"Acts 8:31","short":"Ac 8:31","text":"And he said, \u201cHow can I, unless someone guides me?\u201d And he invited Philip to come up and sit with him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":31},{"ref":"Acts 8:32","short":"Ac 8:32","text":"Now the passage of the Scripture that he was reading was this: \u201cLike a sheep he was led to the slaughter and like a lamb before its shearer is silent, so he opens not his mouth.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":32},{"ref":"Acts 8:33","short":"Ac 8:33","text":"In his humiliation justice was denied him. Who can describe his generation? For his life is taken away from the earth.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":33},{"ref":"Acts 8:34","short":"Ac 8:34","text":"And the eunuch said to Philip, \u201cAbout whom, I ask you, does the prophet say this, about himself or about someone else?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":34},{"ref":"Acts 8:35","short":"Ac 8:35","text":"Then Philip opened his mouth, and beginning with this Scripture he told him the good news about Jesus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":35},{"ref":"Acts 8:36","short":"Ac 8:36","text":"And as they were going along the road they came to some water, and the eunuch said, \u201cSee, here is water! What prevents me from being baptized?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":36},{"ref":"Acts 8:38","short":"Ac 8:38","text":"And he commanded the chariot to stop, and they both went down into the water, Philip and the eunuch, and he baptized him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":38},{"ref":"Acts 8:39","short":"Ac 8:39","text":"And when they came up out of the water, the Spirit of the Lord carried Philip away, and the eunuch saw him no more, and went on his way rejoicing.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":39},{"ref":"Acts 8:40","short":"Ac 8:40","text":"But Philip found himself at Azotus, and as he passed through he preached the gospel to all the towns until he came to Caesarea.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_8.html","book":"Acts","ch":8,"v":40},{"ref":"Acts 9:1","short":"Ac 9:1","text":"But Saul, still breathing threats and murder against the disciples of the Lord, went to the high priest","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 9:2","short":"Ac 9:2","text":"and asked him for letters to the synagogues at Damascus, so that if he found any belonging to the Way, men or women, he might bring them bound to Jerusalem.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 9:3","short":"Ac 9:3","text":"Now as he went on his way, he approached Damascus, and suddenly a light from heaven shone around him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 9:4","short":"Ac 9:4","text":"And falling to the ground, he heard a voice saying to him, \u201cSaul, Saul, why are you persecuting me?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 9:5","short":"Ac 9:5","text":"And he said, \u201cWho are you, Lord?\u201d And he said, \u201cI am Jesus, whom you are persecuting.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 9:6","short":"Ac 9:6","text":"But rise and enter the city, and you will be told what you are to do.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 9:7","short":"Ac 9:7","text":"The men who were traveling with him stood speechless, hearing the voice but seeing no one.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 9:8","short":"Ac 9:8","text":"Saul rose from the ground, and although his eyes were opened, he saw nothing. So they led him by the hand and brought him into Damascus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 9:9","short":"Ac 9:9","text":"And for three days he was without sight, and neither ate nor drank.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 9:10","short":"Ac 9:10","text":"Now there was a disciple at Damascus named Ananias. The Lord said to him in a vision, \u201cAnanias.\u201d And he said, \u201cHere I am, Lord.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 9:11","short":"Ac 9:11","text":"And the Lord said to him, \u201cRise and go to the street called Straight, and at the house of Judas look for a man of Tarsus named Saul, for behold, he is praying,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 9:12","short":"Ac 9:12","text":"and he has seen in a vision a man named Ananias come in and lay his hands on him so that he might regain his sight.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 9:13","short":"Ac 9:13","text":"But Ananias answered, \u201cLord, I have heard from many about this man, how much evil he has done to your saints at Jerusalem.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 9:14","short":"Ac 9:14","text":"And here he has authority from the chief priests to bind all who call on your name.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 9:15","short":"Ac 9:15","text":"But the Lord said to him, \u201cGo, for he is a chosen instrument of mine to carry my name before the Gentiles and kings and the children of Israel.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 9:16","short":"Ac 9:16","text":"For I will show him how much he must suffer for the sake of my name.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 9:17","short":"Ac 9:17","text":"So Ananias departed and entered the house. And laying his hands on him he said, \u201cBrother Saul, the Lord Jesus who appeared to you on the road by which you came has sent me so that you may regain your sight and be filled with the Holy Spirit.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 9:18","short":"Ac 9:18","text":"And immediately something like scales fell from his eyes, and he regained his sight. Then he rose and was baptized;","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 9:19","short":"Ac 9:19","text":"and taking food, he was strengthened. For some days he was with the disciples at Damascus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 9:20","short":"Ac 9:20","text":"And immediately he proclaimed Jesus in the synagogues, saying, \u201cHe is the Son of God.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 9:21","short":"Ac 9:21","text":"And all who heard him were amazed and said, \u201cIs not this the man who made havoc in Jerusalem of those who called upon this name? And has he not come here for this purpose, to bring them bound before the chief priests?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 9:22","short":"Ac 9:22","text":"But Saul increased all the more in strength, and confounded the Jews who lived in Damascus by proving that Jesus was the Christ.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 9:23","short":"Ac 9:23","text":"When many days had passed, the Jews plotted to kill him,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 9:24","short":"Ac 9:24","text":"but their plot became known to Saul. They were watching the gates day and night in order to kill him,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 9:25","short":"Ac 9:25","text":"but his disciples took him by night and let him down through an opening in the wall, lowering him in a basket.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 9:26","short":"Ac 9:26","text":"And when he had come to Jerusalem, he attempted to join the disciples. And they were all afraid of him, for they did not believe that he was a disciple.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 9:27","short":"Ac 9:27","text":"But Barnabas took him and brought him to the apostles and declared to them how on the road he had seen the Lord, who spoke to him, and how at Damascus he had preached boldly in the name of Jesus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 9:28","short":"Ac 9:28","text":"So he went in and out among them at Jerusalem, preaching boldly in the name of the Lord.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 9:29","short":"Ac 9:29","text":"And he spoke and disputed against the Hellenists. But they were seeking to kill him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":29},{"ref":"Acts 9:30","short":"Ac 9:30","text":"And when the brothers learned this, they brought him down to Caesarea and sent him off to Tarsus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":30},{"ref":"Acts 9:31","short":"Ac 9:31","text":"So the church throughout all Judea and Galilee and Samaria had peace and was being built up. And walking in the fear of the Lord and in the comfort of the Holy Spirit, it multiplied.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":31},{"ref":"Acts 9:32","short":"Ac 9:32","text":"Now as Peter went here and there among them all, he came down also to the saints who lived at Lydda.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":32},{"ref":"Acts 9:33","short":"Ac 9:33","text":"There he found a man named Aeneas, bedridden for eight years, who was paralyzed.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":33},{"ref":"Acts 9:34","short":"Ac 9:34","text":"And Peter said to him, \u201cAeneas, Jesus Christ heals you; rise and make your bed.\u201d And immediately he rose.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":34},{"ref":"Acts 9:35","short":"Ac 9:35","text":"And all the residents of Lydda and Sharon saw him, and they turned to the Lord.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":35},{"ref":"Acts 9:36","short":"Ac 9:36","text":"Now there was in Joppa a disciple named Tabitha, which, translated, means Dorcas. She was full of good works and acts of charity.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":36},{"ref":"Acts 9:37","short":"Ac 9:37","text":"In those days she became ill and died, and when they had washed her, they laid her in an upper room.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":37},{"ref":"Acts 9:38","short":"Ac 9:38","text":"Since Lydda was near Joppa, the disciples, hearing that Peter was there, sent two men to him, urging him, \u201cPlease come to us without delay.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":38},{"ref":"Acts 9:39","short":"Ac 9:39","text":"So Peter rose and went with them. And when he arrived, they took him to the upper room. All the widows stood beside him weeping and showing tunics and other garments that Dorcas made while she was with them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":39},{"ref":"Acts 9:40","short":"Ac 9:40","text":"But Peter put them all outside, and knelt down and prayed; and turning to the body he said, \u201cTabitha, arise.\u201d And she opened her eyes, and when she saw Peter she sat up.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":40},{"ref":"Acts 9:41","short":"Ac 9:41","text":"And he gave her his hand and raised her up. Then, calling the saints and widows, he presented her alive.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":41},{"ref":"Acts 9:42","short":"Ac 9:42","text":"And it became known throughout all Joppa, and many believed in the Lord.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":42},{"ref":"Acts 9:43","short":"Ac 9:43","text":"And he stayed in Joppa for many days with one Simon, a tanner.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_9.html","book":"Acts","ch":9,"v":43},{"ref":"Acts 10:1","short":"Ac 10:1","text":"At Caesarea there was a man named Cornelius, a centurion of what was known as the Italian Cohort,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 10:2","short":"Ac 10:2","text":"a devout man who feared God with all his household, gave alms generously to the people, and prayed continually to God.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 10:3","short":"Ac 10:3","text":"About the ninth hour of the day he saw clearly in a vision an angel of God come in and say to him, \u201cCornelius.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 10:4","short":"Ac 10:4","text":"And he stared at him in terror and said, \u201cWhat is it, Lord?\u201d And he said to him, \u201cYour prayers and your alms have ascended as a memorial before God.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 10:5","short":"Ac 10:5","text":"And now send men to Joppa and bring one Simon who is called Peter.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 10:6","short":"Ac 10:6","text":"He is lodging with one Simon, a tanner, whose house is by the sea.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 10:7","short":"Ac 10:7","text":"When the angel who spoke to him had departed, he called two of his servants and a devout soldier from among those who attended him,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 10:8","short":"Ac 10:8","text":"and having related everything to them, he sent them to Joppa.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 10:9","short":"Ac 10:9","text":"The next day, as they were on their journey and approaching the city, Peter went up on the housetop about the sixth hour to pray.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 10:10","short":"Ac 10:10","text":"And he became hungry and wanted something to eat, but while they were preparing it, he fell into a trance","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 10:11","short":"Ac 10:11","text":"and saw the heavens opened and something like a great sheet descending, being let down by its four corners upon the earth.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 10:12","short":"Ac 10:12","text":"In it were all kinds of animals and reptiles and birds of the air.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 10:13","short":"Ac 10:13","text":"And there came a voice to him: \u201cRise, Peter; kill and eat.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 10:14","short":"Ac 10:14","text":"But Peter said, \u201cBy no means, Lord; for I have never eaten anything that is common or unclean.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 10:15","short":"Ac 10:15","text":"And the voice came to him again a second time, \u201cWhat God has made clean, do not call common.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 10:16","short":"Ac 10:16","text":"This happened three times, and the thing was taken up at once to heaven.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 10:17","short":"Ac 10:17","text":"Now while Peter was inwardly perplexed as to what the vision that he had seen might mean, behold, the men who were sent by Cornelius, having made inquiry for Simon\u2019s house, stood at the gate","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 10:18","short":"Ac 10:18","text":"and called out to ask whether Simon who was called Peter was lodging there.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 10:19","short":"Ac 10:19","text":"And while Peter was pondering the vision, the Spirit said to him, \u201cBehold, three men are looking for you.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 10:20","short":"Ac 10:20","text":"Rise and go down and accompany them without hesitation, for I have sent them.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 10:21","short":"Ac 10:21","text":"And Peter went down to the men and said, \u201cI am the one you are looking for. What is the reason for your coming?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 10:22","short":"Ac 10:22","text":"And they said, \u201cCornelius, a centurion, an upright and God-fearing man, who is well spoken of by the whole Jewish nation, was directed by a holy angel to send for you to come to his house and to hear what you have to say.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 10:23","short":"Ac 10:23","text":"So he invited them in to be his guests. The next day he rose and went away with them, and some of the brothers from Joppa accompanied him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 10:24","short":"Ac 10:24","text":"And on the following day they entered Caesarea. Cornelius was expecting them and had called together his relatives and close friends.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 10:25","short":"Ac 10:25","text":"When Peter entered, Cornelius met him and fell down at his feet and worshiped him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 10:26","short":"Ac 10:26","text":"But Peter lifted him up, saying, \u201cStand up; I too am a man.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 10:27","short":"Ac 10:27","text":"And as he talked with him, he went in and found many persons gathered.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 10:28","short":"Ac 10:28","text":"And he said to them, \u201cYou yourselves know how unlawful it is for a Jew to associate with or to visit anyone of another nation, but God has shown me that I should not call any person common or unclean.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 10:29","short":"Ac 10:29","text":"So when I was sent for, I came without objection. I ask then why you sent for me.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":29},{"ref":"Acts 10:30","short":"Ac 10:30","text":"And Cornelius said, \u201cFour days ago, about this hour, I was praying in my house at the ninth hour, and behold, a man stood before me in bright clothing","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":30},{"ref":"Acts 10:31","short":"Ac 10:31","text":"and said, \u2018Cornelius, your prayer has been heard and your alms have been remembered before God.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":31},{"ref":"Acts 10:32","short":"Ac 10:32","text":"Send therefore to Joppa and ask for Simon who is called Peter. He is lodging in the house of Simon, a tanner, by the sea.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":32},{"ref":"Acts 10:33","short":"Ac 10:33","text":"So I sent for you at once, and you have been kind enough to come. Now therefore we are all here in the presence of God to hear all that you have been commanded by the Lord.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":33},{"ref":"Acts 10:34","short":"Ac 10:34","text":"So Peter opened his mouth and said: \u201cTruly I understand that God shows no partiality,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":34},{"ref":"Acts 10:35","short":"Ac 10:35","text":"but in every nation anyone who fears him and does what is right is acceptable to him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":35},{"ref":"Acts 10:36","short":"Ac 10:36","text":"As for the word that he sent to Israel, preaching good news of peace through Jesus Christ (he is Lord of all),","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":36},{"ref":"Acts 10:37","short":"Ac 10:37","text":"you yourselves know what happened throughout all Judea, beginning from Galilee after the baptism that John proclaimed:","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":37},{"ref":"Acts 10:38","short":"Ac 10:38","text":"how God anointed Jesus of Nazareth with the Holy Spirit and with power. He went about doing good and healing all who were oppressed by the devil, for God was with him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":38},{"ref":"Acts 10:39","short":"Ac 10:39","text":"And we are witnesses of all that he did both in the country of the Jews and in Jerusalem. They put him to death by hanging him on a tree,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":39},{"ref":"Acts 10:40","short":"Ac 10:40","text":"but God raised him on the third day and made him to appear,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":40},{"ref":"Acts 10:41","short":"Ac 10:41","text":"not to all the people but to us who had been chosen by God as witnesses, who ate and drank with him after he rose from the dead.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":41},{"ref":"Acts 10:42","short":"Ac 10:42","text":"And he commanded us to preach to the people and to testify that he is the one appointed by God to be judge of the living and the dead.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":42},{"ref":"Acts 10:43","short":"Ac 10:43","text":"To him all the prophets bear witness that everyone who believes in him receives forgiveness of sins through his name.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":43},{"ref":"Acts 10:44","short":"Ac 10:44","text":"While Peter was still saying these things, the Holy Spirit fell on all who heard the word.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":44},{"ref":"Acts 10:45","short":"Ac 10:45","text":"And the believers from among the circumcised who had come with Peter were amazed, because the gift of the Holy Spirit was poured out even on the Gentiles.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":45},{"ref":"Acts 10:46","short":"Ac 10:46","text":"For they were hearing them speaking in tongues and extolling God. Then Peter declared,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":46},{"ref":"Acts 10:47","short":"Ac 10:47","text":"\u201cCan anyone withhold water for baptizing these people, who have received the Holy Spirit just as we have?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":47},{"ref":"Acts 10:48","short":"Ac 10:48","text":"And he commanded them to be baptized in the name of Jesus Christ. Then they asked him to remain for some days.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_10.html","book":"Acts","ch":10,"v":48},{"ref":"Acts 11:1","short":"Ac 11:1","text":"Now the apostles and the brothers who were throughout Judea heard that the Gentiles also had received the word of God.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 11:2","short":"Ac 11:2","text":"So when Peter went up to Jerusalem, the circumcision party criticized him, saying,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 11:3","short":"Ac 11:3","text":"\u201cYou went to uncircumcised men and ate with them.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 11:4","short":"Ac 11:4","text":"But Peter began and explained it to them in order:","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 11:5","short":"Ac 11:5","text":"\u201cI was in the city of Joppa praying, and in a trance I saw a vision, something like a great sheet descending, being let down from heaven by its four corners, and it came down to me.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 11:6","short":"Ac 11:6","text":"Looking at it closely, I observed animals and beasts of prey and reptiles and birds of the air.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 11:7","short":"Ac 11:7","text":"And I heard a voice saying to me, \u2018Rise, Peter; kill and eat.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 11:8","short":"Ac 11:8","text":"But I said, \u2018By no means, Lord; for nothing common or unclean has ever entered my mouth.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 11:9","short":"Ac 11:9","text":"But the voice answered a second time from heaven, \u2018What God has made clean, do not call common.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 11:10","short":"Ac 11:10","text":"This happened three times, and all was drawn up again into heaven.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 11:11","short":"Ac 11:11","text":"And behold, at that very moment three men arrived at the house in which we were, sent to me from Caesarea.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 11:12","short":"Ac 11:12","text":"And the Spirit told me to go with them, making no distinction. These six brothers also accompanied me, and we entered the man\u2019s house.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 11:13","short":"Ac 11:13","text":"And he told us how he had seen the angel stand in his house and say, \u2018Send to Joppa and bring Simon who is called Peter;","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 11:14","short":"Ac 11:14","text":"he will declare to you a message by which you will be saved, you and all your household.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 11:15","short":"Ac 11:15","text":"As I began to speak, the Holy Spirit fell on them just as on us at the beginning.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 11:16","short":"Ac 11:16","text":"And I remembered the word of the Lord, how he said, \u2018John baptized with water, but you will be baptized with the Holy Spirit.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 11:17","short":"Ac 11:17","text":"If then God gave the same gift to them as he gave to us when we believed in the Lord Jesus Christ, who was I that I could stand in God\u2019s way?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 11:18","short":"Ac 11:18","text":"When they heard these things they fell silent. And they glorified God, saying, \u201cThen to the Gentiles also God has granted repentance that leads to life.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 11:19","short":"Ac 11:19","text":"Now those who were scattered because of the persecution that arose over Stephen traveled as far as Phoenicia and Cyprus and Antioch, speaking the word to no one except Jews.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 11:20","short":"Ac 11:20","text":"But there were some of them, men of Cyprus and Cyrene, who on coming to Antioch spoke to the Hellenists also, preaching the Lord Jesus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 11:21","short":"Ac 11:21","text":"And the hand of the Lord was with them, and a great number who believed turned to the Lord.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 11:22","short":"Ac 11:22","text":"The report of this came to the ears of the church in Jerusalem, and they sent Barnabas to Antioch.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 11:23","short":"Ac 11:23","text":"When he came and saw the grace of God, he was glad, and he exhorted them all to remain faithful to the Lord with steadfast purpose,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 11:24","short":"Ac 11:24","text":"for he was a good man, full of the Holy Spirit and of faith. And a great many people were added to the Lord.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 11:25","short":"Ac 11:25","text":"So Barnabas went to Tarsus to look for Saul,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 11:26","short":"Ac 11:26","text":"and when he had found him, he brought him to Antioch. For a whole year they met with the church and taught a great many people. And in Antioch the disciples were first called Christians.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 11:27","short":"Ac 11:27","text":"Now in these days prophets came down from Jerusalem to Antioch.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 11:28","short":"Ac 11:28","text":"And one of them named Agabus stood up and foretold by the Spirit that there would be a great famine over all the world (this took place in the days of Claudius).","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 11:29","short":"Ac 11:29","text":"So the disciples determined, every one according to his ability, to send relief to the brothers living in Judea.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":29},{"ref":"Acts 11:30","short":"Ac 11:30","text":"And they did so, sending it to the elders by the hand of Barnabas and Saul.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_11.html","book":"Acts","ch":11,"v":30},{"ref":"Acts 12:1","short":"Ac 12:1","text":"About that time Herod the king laid violent hands on some who belonged to the church.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 12:2","short":"Ac 12:2","text":"He killed James the brother of John with the sword,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 12:3","short":"Ac 12:3","text":"and when he saw that it pleased the Jews, he proceeded to arrest Peter also. This was during the days of Unleavened Bread.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 12:4","short":"Ac 12:4","text":"And when he had seized him, he put him in prison, delivering him over to four squads of soldiers to guard him, intending after the Passover to bring him out to the people.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 12:5","short":"Ac 12:5","text":"So Peter was kept in prison, but earnest prayer for him was made to God by the church.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 12:6","short":"Ac 12:6","text":"Now when Herod was about to bring him out, on that very night, Peter was sleeping between two soldiers, bound with two chains, and sentries before the door were guarding the prison.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 12:7","short":"Ac 12:7","text":"And behold, an angel of the Lord stood next to him, and a light shone in the cell. He struck Peter on the side and woke him, saying, \u201cGet up quickly.\u201d And the chains fell off his hands.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 12:8","short":"Ac 12:8","text":"And the angel said to him, \u201cDress yourself and put on your sandals.\u201d And he did so. And he said to him, \u201cWrap your cloak around you and follow me.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 12:9","short":"Ac 12:9","text":"And he went out and followed him. He did not know that what was being done by the angel was real, but thought he was seeing a vision.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 12:10","short":"Ac 12:10","text":"When they had passed the first and the second guard, they came to the iron gate leading into the city. It opened for them of its own accord, and they went out and went along one street, and immediately the angel left him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 12:11","short":"Ac 12:11","text":"When Peter came to himself, he said, \u201cNow I am sure that the Lord has sent his angel and rescued me from the hand of Herod and from all that the Jewish people were expecting.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 12:12","short":"Ac 12:12","text":"When he realized this, he went to the house of Mary, the mother of John whose other name was Mark, where many were gathered together and were praying.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 12:13","short":"Ac 12:13","text":"And when he knocked at the door of the gateway, a servant girl named Rhoda came to answer.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 12:14","short":"Ac 12:14","text":"Recognizing Peter\u2019s voice, in her joy she did not open the gate but ran in and reported that Peter was standing at the gate.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 12:15","short":"Ac 12:15","text":"They said to her, \u201cYou are out of your mind.\u201d But she kept insisting that it was so, and they kept saying, \u201cIt is his angel!\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 12:16","short":"Ac 12:16","text":"But Peter continued knocking, and when they opened, they saw him and were amazed.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 12:17","short":"Ac 12:17","text":"But motioning to them with his hand to be silent, he described to them how the Lord had brought him out of the prison. And he said, \u201cTell these things to James and to the brothers.\u201d Then he departed and went to another place.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 12:18","short":"Ac 12:18","text":"Now when day came, there was no little disturbance among the soldiers over what had become of Peter.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 12:19","short":"Ac 12:19","text":"And after Herod searched for him and did not find him, he examined the sentries and ordered that they should be put to death. Then he went down from Judea to Caesarea and spent time there.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 12:20","short":"Ac 12:20","text":"Now Herod was angry with the people of Tyre and Sidon, and they came to him with one accord, and having persuaded Blastus, the king\u2019s chamberlain, they asked for peace, because their country depended on the king\u2019s country for food.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 12:21","short":"Ac 12:21","text":"On an appointed day Herod put on his royal robes, took his seat upon the throne, and delivered an oration to them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 12:22","short":"Ac 12:22","text":"And the people were shouting, \u201cThe voice of a god, and not of a man!\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 12:23","short":"Ac 12:23","text":"Immediately an angel of the Lord struck him down, because he did not give God the glory, and he was eaten by worms and breathed his last.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 12:24","short":"Ac 12:24","text":"But the word of God increased and multiplied.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 12:25","short":"Ac 12:25","text":"And Barnabas and Saul returned from Jerusalem when they had completed their service, bringing with them John, whose other name was Mark.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_12.html","book":"Acts","ch":12,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 13:1","short":"Ac 13:1","text":"Now there were in the church at Antioch prophets and teachers, Barnabas, Simeon who was called Niger, Lucius of Cyrene, Manaen a lifelong friend of Herod the tetrarch, and Saul.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 13:2","short":"Ac 13:2","text":"While they were worshiping the Lord and fasting, the Holy Spirit said, \u201cSet apart for me Barnabas and Saul for the work to which I have called them.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 13:3","short":"Ac 13:3","text":"Then after fasting and praying they laid their hands on them and sent them off.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 13:4","short":"Ac 13:4","text":"So, being sent out by the Holy Spirit, they went down to Seleucia, and from there they sailed to Cyprus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 13:5","short":"Ac 13:5","text":"When they arrived at Salamis, they proclaimed the word of God in the synagogues of the Jews. And they had John to assist them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 13:6","short":"Ac 13:6","text":"When they had gone through the whole island as far as Paphos, they came upon a certain magician, a Jewish false prophet named Bar-Jesus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 13:7","short":"Ac 13:7","text":"He was with the proconsul, Sergius Paulus, a man of intelligence, who summoned Barnabas and Saul and sought to hear the word of God.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 13:8","short":"Ac 13:8","text":"But Elymas the magician (for that is the meaning of his name) opposed them, seeking to turn the proconsul away from the faith.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 13:9","short":"Ac 13:9","text":"But Saul, who was also called Paul, filled with the Holy Spirit, looked intently at him","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 13:10","short":"Ac 13:10","text":"and said, \u201cYou son of the devil, you enemy of all righteousness, full of all deceit and villainy, will you not stop making crooked the straight paths of the Lord?","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 13:11","short":"Ac 13:11","text":"And now, behold, the hand of the Lord is upon you, and you will be blind and unable to see the sun for a time.\u201d Immediately mist and darkness fell upon him, and he went about seeking people to lead him by the hand.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 13:12","short":"Ac 13:12","text":"Then the proconsul believed, when he saw what had occurred, for he was astonished at the teaching of the Lord.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 13:13","short":"Ac 13:13","text":"Now Paul and his companions set sail from Paphos and came to Perga in Pamphylia. And John left them and returned to Jerusalem,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 13:14","short":"Ac 13:14","text":"but they went on from Perga and came to Antioch in Pisidia. And on the Sabbath day they went into the synagogue and sat down.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 13:15","short":"Ac 13:15","text":"After the reading from the Law and the Prophets, the rulers of the synagogue sent a message to them, saying, \u201cBrothers, if you have any word of encouragement for the people, say it.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 13:16","short":"Ac 13:16","text":"So Paul stood up, and motioning with his hand said: \u201cMen of Israel and you who fear God, listen.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 13:17","short":"Ac 13:17","text":"The God of this people Israel chose our fathers and made the people great during their stay in the land of Egypt, and with uplifted arm he led them out of it.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 13:18","short":"Ac 13:18","text":"And for about forty years he put up with them in the wilderness.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 13:19","short":"Ac 13:19","text":"And after destroying seven nations in the land of Canaan, he gave them their land as an inheritance.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 13:20","short":"Ac 13:20","text":"All this took about 450 years. And after that he gave them judges until Samuel the prophet.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 13:21","short":"Ac 13:21","text":"Then they asked for a king, and God gave them Saul the son of Kish, a man of the tribe of Benjamin, for forty years.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 13:22","short":"Ac 13:22","text":"And when he had removed him, he raised up David to be their king, of whom he testified and said, \u2018I have found in David the son of Jesse a man after my heart, who will do all my will.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 13:23","short":"Ac 13:23","text":"Of this man\u2019s offspring God has brought to Israel a Savior, Jesus, as he promised.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 13:24","short":"Ac 13:24","text":"Before his coming, John had proclaimed a baptism of repentance to all the people of Israel.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 13:25","short":"Ac 13:25","text":"And as John was finishing his course, he said, \u2018What do you suppose that I am? I am not he. No, but behold, after me one is coming, the sandals of whose feet I am not worthy to untie.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 13:26","short":"Ac 13:26","text":"\u201cBrothers, sons of the family of Abraham, and those among you who fear God, to us has been sent the message of this salvation.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 13:27","short":"Ac 13:27","text":"For those who live in Jerusalem and their rulers, because they did not recognize him nor understand the utterances of the prophets, which are read every Sabbath, fulfilled them by condemning him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 13:28","short":"Ac 13:28","text":"And though they found in him no guilt worthy of death, they asked Pilate to have him executed.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 13:29","short":"Ac 13:29","text":"And when they had carried out all that was written of him, they took him down from the tree and laid him in a tomb.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":29},{"ref":"Acts 13:30","short":"Ac 13:30","text":"But God raised him from the dead,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":30},{"ref":"Acts 13:31","short":"Ac 13:31","text":"and for many days he appeared to those who had come up with him from Galilee to Jerusalem, who are now his witnesses to the people.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":31},{"ref":"Acts 13:32","short":"Ac 13:32","text":"And we bring you the good news that what God promised to the fathers,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":32},{"ref":"Acts 13:33","short":"Ac 13:33","text":"this he has fulfilled to us their children by raising Jesus, as also it is written in the second Psalm, \u201c\u2018You are my Son, today I have begotten you.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":33},{"ref":"Acts 13:34","short":"Ac 13:34","text":"And as for the fact that he raised him from the dead, no more to return to corruption, he has spoken in this way, \u201c\u2018I will give you the holy and sure blessings of David.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":34},{"ref":"Acts 13:35","short":"Ac 13:35","text":"Therefore he says also in another psalm, \u201c\u2018You will not let your Holy One see corruption.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":35},{"ref":"Acts 13:36","short":"Ac 13:36","text":"For David, after he had served the purpose of God in his own generation, fell asleep and was laid with his fathers and saw corruption,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":36},{"ref":"Acts 13:37","short":"Ac 13:37","text":"but he whom God raised up did not see corruption.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":37},{"ref":"Acts 13:38","short":"Ac 13:38","text":"Let it be known to you therefore, brothers, that through this man forgiveness of sins is proclaimed to you,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":38},{"ref":"Acts 13:39","short":"Ac 13:39","text":"and by him everyone who believes is freed from everything from which you could not be freed by the law of Moses.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":39},{"ref":"Acts 13:40","short":"Ac 13:40","text":"Beware, therefore, lest what is said in the Prophets should come about:","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":40},{"ref":"Acts 13:41","short":"Ac 13:41","text":"\u201c\u2018Look, you scoffers, be astounded and perish; for I am doing a work in your days, a work that you will not believe, even if one tells it to you.\u2019\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":41},{"ref":"Acts 13:42","short":"Ac 13:42","text":"As they went out, the people begged that these things might be told them the next Sabbath.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":42},{"ref":"Acts 13:43","short":"Ac 13:43","text":"And after the meeting of the synagogue broke up, many Jews and devout converts to Judaism followed Paul and Barnabas, who, as they spoke with them, urged them to continue in the grace of God.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":43},{"ref":"Acts 13:44","short":"Ac 13:44","text":"The next Sabbath almost the whole city gathered to hear the word of the Lord.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":44},{"ref":"Acts 13:45","short":"Ac 13:45","text":"But when the Jews saw the crowds, they were filled with jealousy and began to contradict what was spoken by Paul, reviling him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":45},{"ref":"Acts 13:46","short":"Ac 13:46","text":"And Paul and Barnabas spoke out boldly, saying, \u201cIt was necessary that the word of God be spoken first to you. Since you thrust it aside and judge yourselves unworthy of eternal life, behold, we are turning to the Gentiles.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":46},{"ref":"Acts 13:47","short":"Ac 13:47","text":"For so the Lord has commanded us, saying, \u201c\u2018I have made you a light for the Gentiles, that you may bring salvation to the ends of the earth.\u2019\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":47},{"ref":"Acts 13:48","short":"Ac 13:48","text":"And when the Gentiles heard this, they began rejoicing and glorifying the word of the Lord, and as many as were appointed to eternal life believed.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":48},{"ref":"Acts 13:49","short":"Ac 13:49","text":"And the word of the Lord was spreading throughout the whole region.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":49},{"ref":"Acts 13:50","short":"Ac 13:50","text":"But the Jews incited the devout women of high standing and the leading men of the city, stirred up persecution against Paul and Barnabas, and drove them out of their district.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":50},{"ref":"Acts 13:51","short":"Ac 13:51","text":"But they shook off the dust from their feet against them and went to Iconium.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":51},{"ref":"Acts 13:52","short":"Ac 13:52","text":"And the disciples were filled with joy and with the Holy Spirit.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_13.html","book":"Acts","ch":13,"v":52},{"ref":"Acts 14:1","short":"Ac 14:1","text":"Now at Iconium they entered together into the Jewish synagogue and spoke in such a way that a great number of both Jews and Greeks believed.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 14:2","short":"Ac 14:2","text":"But the unbelieving Jews stirred up the Gentiles and poisoned their minds against the brothers.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 14:3","short":"Ac 14:3","text":"So they remained for a long time, speaking boldly for the Lord, who bore witness to the word of his grace, granting signs and wonders to be done by their hands.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 14:4","short":"Ac 14:4","text":"But the people of the city were divided; some sided with the Jews and some with the apostles.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 14:5","short":"Ac 14:5","text":"When an attempt was made by both Gentiles and Jews, with their rulers, to mistreat them and to stone them,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 14:6","short":"Ac 14:6","text":"they learned of it and fled to Lystra and Derbe, cities of Lycaonia, and to the surrounding country,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 14:7","short":"Ac 14:7","text":"and there they continued to preach the gospel.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 14:8","short":"Ac 14:8","text":"Now at Lystra there was a man sitting who could not use his feet. He was crippled from birth and had never walked.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 14:9","short":"Ac 14:9","text":"He listened to Paul speaking. And Paul, looking intently at him and seeing that he had faith to be made well,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 14:10","short":"Ac 14:10","text":"said in a loud voice, \u201cStand upright on your feet.\u201d And he sprang up and began walking.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 14:11","short":"Ac 14:11","text":"And when the crowds saw what Paul had done, they lifted up their voices, saying in Lycaonian, \u201cThe gods have come down to us in the likeness of men!\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 14:12","short":"Ac 14:12","text":"Barnabas they called Zeus, and Paul, Hermes, because he was the chief speaker.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 14:13","short":"Ac 14:13","text":"And the priest of Zeus, whose temple was at the entrance to the city, brought oxen and garlands to the gates and wanted to offer sacrifice with the crowds.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 14:14","short":"Ac 14:14","text":"But when the apostles Barnabas and Paul heard of it, they tore their garments and rushed out into the crowd, crying out,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 14:15","short":"Ac 14:15","text":"\u201cMen, why are you doing these things? We also are men, of like nature with you, and we bring you good news, that you should turn from these vain things to a living God, who made the heaven and the earth and the sea and all that is in them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 14:16","short":"Ac 14:16","text":"In past generations he allowed all the nations to walk in their own ways.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 14:17","short":"Ac 14:17","text":"Yet he did not leave himself without witness, for he did good by giving you rains from heaven and fruitful seasons, satisfying your hearts with food and gladness.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 14:18","short":"Ac 14:18","text":"Even with these words they scarcely restrained the people from offering sacrifice to them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 14:19","short":"Ac 14:19","text":"But Jews came from Antioch and Iconium, and having persuaded the crowds, they stoned Paul and dragged him out of the city, supposing that he was dead.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 14:20","short":"Ac 14:20","text":"But when the disciples gathered about him, he rose up and entered the city, and on the next day he went on with Barnabas to Derbe.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 14:21","short":"Ac 14:21","text":"When they had preached the gospel to that city and had made many disciples, they returned to Lystra and to Iconium and to Antioch,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 14:22","short":"Ac 14:22","text":"strengthening the souls of the disciples, encouraging them to continue in the faith, and saying that through many tribulations we must enter the kingdom of God.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 14:23","short":"Ac 14:23","text":"And when they had appointed elders for them in every church, with prayer and fasting they committed them to the Lord in whom they had believed.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 14:24","short":"Ac 14:24","text":"Then they passed through Pisidia and came to Pamphylia.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 14:25","short":"Ac 14:25","text":"And when they had spoken the word in Perga, they went down to Attalia,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 14:26","short":"Ac 14:26","text":"and from there they sailed to Antioch, where they had been commended to the grace of God for the work that they had fulfilled.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 14:27","short":"Ac 14:27","text":"And when they arrived and gathered the church together, they declared all that God had done with them, and how he had opened a door of faith to the Gentiles.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 14:28","short":"Ac 14:28","text":"And they remained no little time with the disciples.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_14.html","book":"Acts","ch":14,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 15:1","short":"Ac 15:1","text":"But some men came down from Judea and were teaching the brothers, \u201cUnless you are circumcised according to the custom of Moses, you cannot be saved.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 15:2","short":"Ac 15:2","text":"And after Paul and Barnabas had no small dissension and debate with them, Paul and Barnabas and some of the others were appointed to go up to Jerusalem to the apostles and the elders about this question.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 15:3","short":"Ac 15:3","text":"So, being sent on their way by the church, they passed through both Phoenicia and Samaria, describing in detail the conversion of the Gentiles, and brought great joy to all the brothers.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 15:4","short":"Ac 15:4","text":"When they came to Jerusalem, they were welcomed by the church and the apostles and the elders, and they declared all that God had done with them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 15:5","short":"Ac 15:5","text":"But some believers who belonged to the party of the Pharisees rose up and said, \u201cIt is necessary to circumcise them and to order them to keep the law of Moses.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 15:6","short":"Ac 15:6","text":"The apostles and the elders were gathered together to consider this matter.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 15:7","short":"Ac 15:7","text":"And after there had been much debate, Peter stood up and said to them, \u201cBrothers, you know that in the early days God made a choice among you, that by my mouth the Gentiles should hear the word of the gospel and believe.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 15:8","short":"Ac 15:8","text":"And God, who knows the heart, bore witness to them, by giving them the Holy Spirit just as he did to us,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 15:9","short":"Ac 15:9","text":"and he made no distinction between us and them, having cleansed their hearts by faith.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 15:10","short":"Ac 15:10","text":"Now, therefore, why are you putting God to the test by placing a yoke on the neck of the disciples that neither our fathers nor we have been able to bear?","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 15:11","short":"Ac 15:11","text":"But we believe that we will be saved through the grace of the Lord Jesus, just as they will.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 15:12","short":"Ac 15:12","text":"And all the assembly fell silent, and they listened to Barnabas and Paul as they related what signs and wonders God had done through them among the Gentiles.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 15:13","short":"Ac 15:13","text":"After they finished speaking, James replied, \u201cBrothers, listen to me.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 15:14","short":"Ac 15:14","text":"Simeon has related how God first visited the Gentiles, to take from them a people for his name.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 15:15","short":"Ac 15:15","text":"And with this the words of the prophets agree, just as it is written,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 15:16","short":"Ac 15:16","text":"\u201c\u2018After this I will return, and I will rebuild the tent of David that has fallen; I will rebuild its ruins, and I will restore it,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 15:17","short":"Ac 15:17","text":"that the remnant of mankind may seek the Lord, and all the Gentiles who are called by my name, says the Lord, who makes these things","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 15:18","short":"Ac 15:18","text":"known from of old.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 15:19","short":"Ac 15:19","text":"Therefore my judgment is that we should not trouble those of the Gentiles who turn to God,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 15:20","short":"Ac 15:20","text":"but should write to them to abstain from the things polluted by idols, and from sexual immorality, and from what has been strangled, and from blood.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 15:21","short":"Ac 15:21","text":"For from ancient generations Moses has had in every city those who proclaim him, for he is read every Sabbath in the synagogues.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 15:22","short":"Ac 15:22","text":"Then it seemed good to the apostles and the elders, with the whole church, to choose men from among them and send them to Antioch with Paul and Barnabas. They sent Judas called Barsabbas, and Silas, leading men among the brothers,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 15:23","short":"Ac 15:23","text":"with the following letter: \u201cThe brothers, both the apostles and the elders, to the brothers who are of the Gentiles in Antioch and Syria and Cilicia, greetings.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 15:24","short":"Ac 15:24","text":"Since we have heard that some persons have gone out from us and troubled you with words, unsettling your minds, although we gave them no instructions,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 15:25","short":"Ac 15:25","text":"it has seemed good to us, having come to one accord, to choose men and send them to you with our beloved Barnabas and Paul,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 15:26","short":"Ac 15:26","text":"men who have risked their lives for the name of our Lord Jesus Christ.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 15:27","short":"Ac 15:27","text":"We have therefore sent Judas and Silas, who themselves will tell you the same things by word of mouth.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 15:28","short":"Ac 15:28","text":"For it has seemed good to the Holy Spirit and to us to lay on you no greater burden than these requirements:","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 15:29","short":"Ac 15:29","text":"that you abstain from what has been sacrificed to idols, and from blood, and from what has been strangled, and from sexual immorality. If you keep yourselves from these, you will do well. Farewell.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":29},{"ref":"Acts 15:30","short":"Ac 15:30","text":"So when they were sent off, they went down to Antioch, and having gathered the congregation together, they delivered the letter.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":30},{"ref":"Acts 15:31","short":"Ac 15:31","text":"And when they had read it, they rejoiced because of its encouragement.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":31},{"ref":"Acts 15:32","short":"Ac 15:32","text":"And Judas and Silas, who were themselves prophets, encouraged and strengthened the brothers with many words.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":32},{"ref":"Acts 15:33","short":"Ac 15:33","text":"And after they had spent some time, they were sent off in peace by the brothers to those who had sent them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":33},{"ref":"Acts 15:35","short":"Ac 15:35","text":"But Paul and Barnabas remained in Antioch, teaching and preaching the word of the Lord, with many others also.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":35},{"ref":"Acts 15:36","short":"Ac 15:36","text":"And after some days Paul said to Barnabas, \u201cLet us return and visit the brothers in every city where we proclaimed the word of the Lord, and see how they are.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":36},{"ref":"Acts 15:37","short":"Ac 15:37","text":"Now Barnabas wanted to take with them John called Mark.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":37},{"ref":"Acts 15:38","short":"Ac 15:38","text":"But Paul thought best not to take with them one who had withdrawn from them in Pamphylia and had not gone with them to the work.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":38},{"ref":"Acts 15:39","short":"Ac 15:39","text":"And there arose a sharp disagreement, so that they separated from each other. Barnabas took Mark with him and sailed away to Cyprus,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":39},{"ref":"Acts 15:40","short":"Ac 15:40","text":"but Paul chose Silas and departed, having been commended by the brothers to the grace of the Lord.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":40},{"ref":"Acts 15:41","short":"Ac 15:41","text":"And he went through Syria and Cilicia, strengthening the churches.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_15.html","book":"Acts","ch":15,"v":41},{"ref":"Acts 16:1","short":"Ac 16:1","text":"Paul came also to Derbe and to Lystra. A disciple was there, named Timothy, the son of a Jewish woman who was a believer, but his father was a Greek.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 16:2","short":"Ac 16:2","text":"He was well spoken of by the brothers at Lystra and Iconium.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 16:3","short":"Ac 16:3","text":"Paul wanted Timothy to accompany him, and he took him and circumcised him because of the Jews who were in those places, for they all knew that his father was a Greek.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 16:4","short":"Ac 16:4","text":"As they went on their way through the cities, they delivered to them for observance the decisions that had been reached by the apostles and elders who were in Jerusalem.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 16:5","short":"Ac 16:5","text":"So the churches were strengthened in the faith, and they increased in numbers daily.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 16:6","short":"Ac 16:6","text":"And they went through the region of Phrygia and Galatia, having been forbidden by the Holy Spirit to speak the word in Asia.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 16:7","short":"Ac 16:7","text":"And when they had come up to Mysia, they attempted to go into Bithynia, but the Spirit of Jesus did not allow them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 16:8","short":"Ac 16:8","text":"So, passing by Mysia, they went down to Troas.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 16:9","short":"Ac 16:9","text":"And a vision appeared to Paul in the night: a man of Macedonia was standing there, urging him and saying, \u201cCome over to Macedonia and help us.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 16:10","short":"Ac 16:10","text":"And when Paul had seen the vision, immediately we sought to go on into Macedonia, concluding that God had called us to preach the gospel to them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 16:11","short":"Ac 16:11","text":"So, setting sail from Troas, we made a direct voyage to Samothrace, and the following day to Neapolis,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 16:12","short":"Ac 16:12","text":"and from there to Philippi, which is a leading city of the district of Macedonia and a Roman colony. We remained in this city some days.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 16:13","short":"Ac 16:13","text":"And on the Sabbath day we went outside the gate to the riverside, where we supposed there was a place of prayer, and we sat down and spoke to the women who had come together.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 16:14","short":"Ac 16:14","text":"One who heard us was a woman named Lydia, from the city of Thyatira, a seller of purple goods, who was a worshiper of God. The Lord opened her heart to pay attention to what was said by Paul.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 16:15","short":"Ac 16:15","text":"And after she was baptized, and her household as well, she urged us, saying, \u201cIf you have judged me to be faithful to the Lord, come to my house and stay.\u201d And she prevailed upon us.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 16:16","short":"Ac 16:16","text":"As we were going to the place of prayer, we were met by a slave girl who had a spirit of divination and brought her owners much gain by fortune-telling.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 16:17","short":"Ac 16:17","text":"She followed Paul and us, crying out, \u201cThese men are servants of the Most High God, who proclaim to you the way of salvation.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 16:18","short":"Ac 16:18","text":"And this she kept doing for many days. Paul, having become greatly annoyed, turned and said to the spirit, \u201cI command you in the name of Jesus Christ to come out of her.\u201d And it came out that very hour.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 16:19","short":"Ac 16:19","text":"But when her owners saw that their hope of gain was gone, they seized Paul and Silas and dragged them into the marketplace before the rulers.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 16:20","short":"Ac 16:20","text":"And when they had brought them to the magistrates, they said, \u201cThese men are Jews, and they are disturbing our city.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 16:21","short":"Ac 16:21","text":"They advocate customs that are not lawful for us as Romans to accept or practice.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 16:22","short":"Ac 16:22","text":"The crowd joined in attacking them, and the magistrates tore the garments off them and gave orders to beat them with rods.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 16:23","short":"Ac 16:23","text":"And when they had inflicted many blows upon them, they threw them into prison, ordering the jailer to keep them safely.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 16:24","short":"Ac 16:24","text":"Having received this order, he put them into the inner prison and fastened their feet in the stocks.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 16:25","short":"Ac 16:25","text":"About midnight Paul and Silas were praying and singing hymns to God, and the prisoners were listening to them,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 16:26","short":"Ac 16:26","text":"and suddenly there was a great earthquake, so that the foundations of the prison were shaken. And immediately all the doors were opened, and everyone\u2019s bonds were unfastened.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 16:27","short":"Ac 16:27","text":"When the jailer woke and saw that the prison doors were open, he drew his sword and was about to kill himself, supposing that the prisoners had escaped.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 16:28","short":"Ac 16:28","text":"But Paul cried with a loud voice, \u201cDo not harm yourself, for we are all here.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 16:29","short":"Ac 16:29","text":"And the jailer called for lights and rushed in, and trembling with fear he fell down before Paul and Silas.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":29},{"ref":"Acts 16:30","short":"Ac 16:30","text":"Then he brought them out and said, \u201cSirs, what must I do to be saved?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":30},{"ref":"Acts 16:31","short":"Ac 16:31","text":"And they said, \u201cBelieve in the Lord Jesus, and you will be saved, you and your household.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":31},{"ref":"Acts 16:32","short":"Ac 16:32","text":"And they spoke the word of the Lord to him and to all who were in his house.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":32},{"ref":"Acts 16:33","short":"Ac 16:33","text":"And he took them the same hour of the night and washed their wounds; and he was baptized at once, he and all his family.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":33},{"ref":"Acts 16:34","short":"Ac 16:34","text":"Then he brought them up into his house and set food before them. And he rejoiced along with his entire household that he had believed in God.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":34},{"ref":"Acts 16:35","short":"Ac 16:35","text":"But when it was day, the magistrates sent the police, saying, \u201cLet those men go.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":35},{"ref":"Acts 16:36","short":"Ac 16:36","text":"And the jailer reported these words to Paul, saying, \u201cThe magistrates have sent to let you go. Therefore come out now and go in peace.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":36},{"ref":"Acts 16:37","short":"Ac 16:37","text":"But Paul said to them, \u201cThey have beaten us publicly, uncondemned, men who are Roman citizens, and have thrown us into prison; and do they now throw us out secretly? No! Let them come themselves and take us out.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":37},{"ref":"Acts 16:38","short":"Ac 16:38","text":"The police reported these words to the magistrates, and they were afraid when they heard that they were Roman citizens.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":38},{"ref":"Acts 16:39","short":"Ac 16:39","text":"So they came and apologized to them. And they took them out and asked them to leave the city.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":39},{"ref":"Acts 16:40","short":"Ac 16:40","text":"So they went out of the prison and visited Lydia. And when they had seen the brothers, they encouraged them and departed.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_16.html","book":"Acts","ch":16,"v":40},{"ref":"Acts 17:1","short":"Ac 17:1","text":"Now when they had passed through Amphipolis and Apollonia, they came to Thessalonica, where there was a synagogue of the Jews.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 17:2","short":"Ac 17:2","text":"And Paul went in, as was his custom, and on three Sabbath days he reasoned with them from the Scriptures,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 17:3","short":"Ac 17:3","text":"explaining and proving that it was necessary for the Christ to suffer and to rise from the dead, and saying, \u201cThis Jesus, whom I proclaim to you, is the Christ.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 17:4","short":"Ac 17:4","text":"And some of them were persuaded and joined Paul and Silas, as did a great many of the devout Greeks and not a few of the leading women.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 17:5","short":"Ac 17:5","text":"But the Jews were jealous, and taking some wicked men of the rabble, they formed a mob, set the city in an uproar, and attacked the house of Jason, seeking to bring them out to the crowd.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 17:6","short":"Ac 17:6","text":"And when they could not find them, they dragged Jason and some of the brothers before the city authorities, shouting, \u201cThese men who have turned the world upside down have come here also,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 17:7","short":"Ac 17:7","text":"and Jason has received them, and they are all acting against the decrees of Caesar, saying that there is another king, Jesus.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 17:8","short":"Ac 17:8","text":"And the people and the city authorities were disturbed when they heard these things.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 17:9","short":"Ac 17:9","text":"And when they had taken money as security from Jason and the rest, they let them go.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 17:10","short":"Ac 17:10","text":"The brothers immediately sent Paul and Silas away by night to Berea, and when they arrived they went into the Jewish synagogue.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 17:11","short":"Ac 17:11","text":"Now these Jews were more noble than those in Thessalonica; they received the word with all eagerness, examining the Scriptures daily to see if these things were so.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 17:12","short":"Ac 17:12","text":"Many of them therefore believed, with not a few Greek women of high standing as well as men.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 17:13","short":"Ac 17:13","text":"But when the Jews from Thessalonica learned that the word of God was proclaimed by Paul at Berea also, they came there too, agitating and stirring up the crowds.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 17:14","short":"Ac 17:14","text":"Then the brothers immediately sent Paul off on his way to the sea, but Silas and Timothy remained there.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 17:15","short":"Ac 17:15","text":"Those who conducted Paul brought him as far as Athens, and after receiving a command for Silas and Timothy to come to him as soon as possible, they departed.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 17:16","short":"Ac 17:16","text":"Now while Paul was waiting for them at Athens, his spirit was provoked within him as he saw that the city was full of idols.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 17:17","short":"Ac 17:17","text":"So he reasoned in the synagogue with the Jews and the devout persons, and in the marketplace every day with those who happened to be there.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 17:18","short":"Ac 17:18","text":"Some of the Epicurean and Stoic philosophers also conversed with him. And some said, \u201cWhat does this babbler wish to say?\u201d Others said, \u201cHe seems to be a preacher of foreign divinities\u201d\u2014because he was preaching Jesus and the resurrection.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 17:19","short":"Ac 17:19","text":"And they took him and brought him to the Areopagus, saying, \u201cMay we know what this new teaching is that you are presenting?","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 17:20","short":"Ac 17:20","text":"For you bring some strange things to our ears. We wish to know therefore what these things mean.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 17:21","short":"Ac 17:21","text":"Now all the Athenians and the foreigners who lived there would spend their time in nothing except telling or hearing something new.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 17:22","short":"Ac 17:22","text":"So Paul, standing in the midst of the Areopagus, said: \u201cMen of Athens, I perceive that in every way you are very religious.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 17:23","short":"Ac 17:23","text":"For as I passed along and observed the objects of your worship, I found also an altar with this inscription: \u2018To the unknown god.\u2019 What therefore you worship as unknown, this I proclaim to you.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 17:24","short":"Ac 17:24","text":"The God who made the world and everything in it, being Lord of heaven and earth, does not live in temples made by man,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 17:25","short":"Ac 17:25","text":"nor is he served by human hands, as though he needed anything, since he himself gives to all mankind life and breath and everything.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 17:26","short":"Ac 17:26","text":"And he made from one man every nation of mankind to live on all the face of the earth, having determined allotted periods and the boundaries of their dwelling place,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 17:27","short":"Ac 17:27","text":"that they should seek God, and perhaps feel their way toward him and find him. Yet he is actually not far from each one of us,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 17:28","short":"Ac 17:28","text":"for \u201c\u2018In him we live and move and have our being\u2019; as even some of your own poets have said, \u201c\u2018For we are indeed his offspring.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 17:29","short":"Ac 17:29","text":"Being then God\u2019s offspring, we ought not to think that the divine being is like gold or silver or stone, an image formed by the art and imagination of man.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":29},{"ref":"Acts 17:30","short":"Ac 17:30","text":"The times of ignorance God overlooked, but now he commands all people everywhere to repent,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":30},{"ref":"Acts 17:31","short":"Ac 17:31","text":"because he has fixed a day on which he will judge the world in righteousness by a man whom he has appointed; and of this he has given assurance to all by raising him from the dead.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":31},{"ref":"Acts 17:32","short":"Ac 17:32","text":"Now when they heard of the resurrection of the dead, some mocked. But others said, \u201cWe will hear you again about this.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":32},{"ref":"Acts 17:33","short":"Ac 17:33","text":"So Paul went out from their midst.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":33},{"ref":"Acts 17:34","short":"Ac 17:34","text":"But some men joined him and believed, among whom also were Dionysius the Areopagite and a woman named Damaris and others with them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_17.html","book":"Acts","ch":17,"v":34},{"ref":"Acts 18:1","short":"Ac 18:1","text":"After this Paul left Athens and went to Corinth.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 18:2","short":"Ac 18:2","text":"And he found a Jew named Aquila, a native of Pontus, recently come from Italy with his wife Priscilla, because Claudius had commanded all the Jews to leave Rome. And he went to see them,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 18:3","short":"Ac 18:3","text":"and because he was of the same trade he stayed with them and worked, for they were tentmakers by trade.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 18:4","short":"Ac 18:4","text":"And he reasoned in the synagogue every Sabbath, and tried to persuade Jews and Greeks.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 18:5","short":"Ac 18:5","text":"When Silas and Timothy arrived from Macedonia, Paul was occupied with the word, testifying to the Jews that the Christ was Jesus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 18:6","short":"Ac 18:6","text":"And when they opposed and reviled him, he shook out his garments and said to them, \u201cYour blood be on your own heads! I am innocent. From now on I will go to the Gentiles.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 18:7","short":"Ac 18:7","text":"And he left there and went to the house of a man named Titius Justus, a worshiper of God. His house was next door to the synagogue.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 18:8","short":"Ac 18:8","text":"Crispus, the ruler of the synagogue, believed in the Lord, together with his entire household. And many of the Corinthians hearing Paul believed and were baptized.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 18:9","short":"Ac 18:9","text":"And the Lord said to Paul one night in a vision, \u201cDo not be afraid, but go on speaking and do not be silent,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 18:10","short":"Ac 18:10","text":"for I am with you, and no one will attack you to harm you, for I have many in this city who are my people.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 18:11","short":"Ac 18:11","text":"And he stayed a year and six months, teaching the word of God among them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 18:12","short":"Ac 18:12","text":"But when Gallio was proconsul of Achaia, the Jews made a united attack on Paul and brought him before the tribunal,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 18:13","short":"Ac 18:13","text":"saying, \u201cThis man is persuading people to worship God contrary to the law.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 18:14","short":"Ac 18:14","text":"But when Paul was about to open his mouth, Gallio said to the Jews, \u201cIf it were a matter of wrongdoing or vicious crime, O Jews, I would have reason to accept your complaint.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 18:15","short":"Ac 18:15","text":"But since it is a matter of questions about words and names and your own law, see to it yourselves. I refuse to be a judge of these things.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 18:16","short":"Ac 18:16","text":"And he drove them from the tribunal.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 18:17","short":"Ac 18:17","text":"And they all seized Sosthenes, the ruler of the synagogue, and beat him in front of the tribunal. But Gallio paid no attention to any of this.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 18:18","short":"Ac 18:18","text":"After this, Paul stayed many days longer and then took leave of the brothers and set sail for Syria, and with him Priscilla and Aquila. At Cenchreae he had cut his hair, for he was under a vow.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 18:19","short":"Ac 18:19","text":"And they came to Ephesus, and he left them there, but he himself went into the synagogue and reasoned with the Jews.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 18:20","short":"Ac 18:20","text":"When they asked him to stay for a longer period, he declined.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 18:21","short":"Ac 18:21","text":"But on taking leave of them he said, \u201cI will return to you if God wills,\u201d and he set sail from Ephesus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 18:22","short":"Ac 18:22","text":"When he had landed at Caesarea, he went up and greeted the church, and then went down to Antioch.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 18:23","short":"Ac 18:23","text":"After spending some time there, he departed and went from one place to the next through the region of Galatia and Phrygia, strengthening all the disciples.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 18:24","short":"Ac 18:24","text":"Now a Jew named Apollos, a native of Alexandria, came to Ephesus. He was an eloquent man, competent in the Scriptures.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 18:25","short":"Ac 18:25","text":"He had been instructed in the way of the Lord. And being fervent in spirit, he spoke and taught accurately the things concerning Jesus, though he knew only the baptism of John.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 18:26","short":"Ac 18:26","text":"He began to speak boldly in the synagogue, but when Priscilla and Aquila heard him, they took him aside and explained to him the way of God more accurately.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 18:27","short":"Ac 18:27","text":"And when he wished to cross to Achaia, the brothers encouraged him and wrote to the disciples to welcome him. When he arrived, he greatly helped those who through grace had believed,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 18:28","short":"Ac 18:28","text":"for he powerfully refuted the Jews in public, showing by the Scriptures that the Christ was Jesus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_18.html","book":"Acts","ch":18,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 19:1","short":"Ac 19:1","text":"And it happened that while Apollos was at Corinth, Paul passed through the inland country and came to Ephesus. There he found some disciples.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 19:2","short":"Ac 19:2","text":"And he said to them, \u201cDid you receive the Holy Spirit when you believed?\u201d And they said, \u201cNo, we have not even heard that there is a Holy Spirit.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 19:3","short":"Ac 19:3","text":"And he said, \u201cInto what then were you baptized?\u201d They said, \u201cInto John\u2019s baptism.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 19:4","short":"Ac 19:4","text":"And Paul said, \u201cJohn baptized with the baptism of repentance, telling the people to believe in the one who was to come after him, that is, Jesus.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 19:5","short":"Ac 19:5","text":"On hearing this, they were baptized in the name of the Lord Jesus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 19:6","short":"Ac 19:6","text":"And when Paul had laid his hands on them, the Holy Spirit came on them, and they began speaking in tongues and prophesying.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 19:7","short":"Ac 19:7","text":"There were about twelve men in all.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 19:8","short":"Ac 19:8","text":"And he entered the synagogue and for three months spoke boldly, reasoning and persuading them about the kingdom of God.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 19:9","short":"Ac 19:9","text":"But when some became stubborn and continued in unbelief, speaking evil of the Way before the congregation, he withdrew from them and took the disciples with him, reasoning daily in the hall of Tyrannus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 19:10","short":"Ac 19:10","text":"This continued for two years, so that all the residents of Asia heard the word of the Lord, both Jews and Greeks.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 19:11","short":"Ac 19:11","text":"And God was doing extraordinary miracles by the hands of Paul,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 19:12","short":"Ac 19:12","text":"so that even handkerchiefs or aprons that had touched his skin were carried away to the sick, and their diseases left them and the evil spirits came out of them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 19:13","short":"Ac 19:13","text":"Then some of the itinerant Jewish exorcists undertook to invoke the name of the Lord Jesus over those who had evil spirits, saying, \u201cI adjure you by the Jesus whom Paul proclaims.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 19:14","short":"Ac 19:14","text":"Seven sons of a Jewish high priest named Sceva were doing this.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 19:15","short":"Ac 19:15","text":"But the evil spirit answered them, \u201cJesus I know, and Paul I recognize, but who are you?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 19:16","short":"Ac 19:16","text":"And the man in whom was the evil spirit leaped on them, mastered all of them and overpowered them, so that they fled out of that house naked and wounded.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 19:17","short":"Ac 19:17","text":"And this became known to all the residents of Ephesus, both Jews and Greeks. And fear fell upon them all, and the name of the Lord Jesus was extolled.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 19:18","short":"Ac 19:18","text":"Also many of those who were now believers came, confessing and divulging their practices.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 19:19","short":"Ac 19:19","text":"And a number of those who had practiced magic arts brought their books together and burned them in the sight of all. And they counted the value of them and found it came to fifty thousand pieces of silver.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 19:20","short":"Ac 19:20","text":"So the word of the Lord continued to increase and prevail mightily.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 19:21","short":"Ac 19:21","text":"Now after these events Paul resolved in the Spirit to pass through Macedonia and Achaia and go to Jerusalem, saying, \u201cAfter I have been there, I must also see Rome.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 19:22","short":"Ac 19:22","text":"And having sent into Macedonia two of his helpers, Timothy and Erastus, he himself stayed in Asia for a while.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 19:23","short":"Ac 19:23","text":"About that time there arose no little disturbance concerning the Way.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 19:24","short":"Ac 19:24","text":"For a man named Demetrius, a silversmith, who made silver shrines of Artemis, brought no little business to the craftsmen.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 19:25","short":"Ac 19:25","text":"These he gathered together, with the workmen in similar trades, and said, \u201cMen, you know that from this business we have our wealth.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 19:26","short":"Ac 19:26","text":"And you see and hear that not only in Ephesus but in almost all of Asia this Paul has persuaded and turned away a great many people, saying that gods made with hands are not gods.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 19:27","short":"Ac 19:27","text":"And there is danger not only that this trade of ours may come into disrepute but also that the temple of the great goddess Artemis may be counted as nothing, and that she may even be deposed from her magnificence, she whom all Asia and the world worship.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 19:28","short":"Ac 19:28","text":"When they heard this they were enraged and were crying out, \u201cGreat is Artemis of the Ephesians!\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 19:29","short":"Ac 19:29","text":"So the city was filled with the confusion, and they rushed together into the theater, dragging with them Gaius and Aristarchus, Macedonians who were Paul\u2019s companions in travel.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":29},{"ref":"Acts 19:30","short":"Ac 19:30","text":"But when Paul wished to go in among the crowd, the disciples would not let him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":30},{"ref":"Acts 19:31","short":"Ac 19:31","text":"And even some of the Asiarchs, who were friends of his, sent to him and were urging him not to venture into the theater.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":31},{"ref":"Acts 19:32","short":"Ac 19:32","text":"Now some cried out one thing, some another, for the assembly was in confusion, and most of them did not know why they had come together.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":32},{"ref":"Acts 19:33","short":"Ac 19:33","text":"Some of the crowd prompted Alexander, whom the Jews had put forward. And Alexander, motioning with his hand, wanted to make a defense to the crowd.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":33},{"ref":"Acts 19:34","short":"Ac 19:34","text":"But when they recognized that he was a Jew, for about two hours they all cried out with one voice, \u201cGreat is Artemis of the Ephesians!\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":34},{"ref":"Acts 19:35","short":"Ac 19:35","text":"And when the town clerk had quieted the crowd, he said, \u201cMen of Ephesus, who is there who does not know that the city of the Ephesians is temple keeper of the great Artemis, and of the sacred stone that fell from the sky?","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":35},{"ref":"Acts 19:36","short":"Ac 19:36","text":"Seeing then that these things cannot be denied, you ought to be quiet and do nothing rash.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":36},{"ref":"Acts 19:37","short":"Ac 19:37","text":"For you have brought these men here who are neither sacrilegious nor blasphemers of our goddess.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":37},{"ref":"Acts 19:38","short":"Ac 19:38","text":"If therefore Demetrius and the craftsmen with him have a complaint against anyone, the courts are open, and there are proconsuls. Let them bring charges against one another.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":38},{"ref":"Acts 19:39","short":"Ac 19:39","text":"But if you seek anything further, it shall be settled in the regular assembly.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":39},{"ref":"Acts 19:40","short":"Ac 19:40","text":"For we really are in danger of being charged with rioting today, since there is no cause that we can give to justify this commotion.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":40},{"ref":"Acts 19:41","short":"Ac 19:41","text":"And when he had said these things, he dismissed the assembly.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_19.html","book":"Acts","ch":19,"v":41},{"ref":"Acts 20:1","short":"Ac 20:1","text":"After the uproar ceased, Paul sent for the disciples, and after encouraging them, he said farewell and departed for Macedonia.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 20:2","short":"Ac 20:2","text":"When he had gone through those regions and had given them much encouragement, he came to Greece.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 20:3","short":"Ac 20:3","text":"There he spent three months, and when a plot was made against him by the Jews as he was about to set sail for Syria, he decided to return through Macedonia.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 20:4","short":"Ac 20:4","text":"Sopater the Berean, son of Pyrrhus, accompanied him; and of the Thessalonians, Aristarchus and Secundus; and Gaius of Derbe, and Timothy; and the Asians, Tychicus and Trophimus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 20:5","short":"Ac 20:5","text":"These went on ahead and were waiting for us at Troas,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 20:6","short":"Ac 20:6","text":"but we sailed away from Philippi after the days of Unleavened Bread, and in five days we came to them at Troas, where we stayed for seven days.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 20:7","short":"Ac 20:7","text":"On the first day of the week, when we were gathered together to break bread, Paul talked with them, intending to depart on the next day, and he prolonged his speech until midnight.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 20:8","short":"Ac 20:8","text":"There were many lamps in the upper room where we were gathered.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 20:9","short":"Ac 20:9","text":"And a young man named Eutychus, sitting at the window, sank into a deep sleep as Paul talked still longer. And being overcome by sleep, he fell down from the third story and was taken up dead.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 20:10","short":"Ac 20:10","text":"But Paul went down and bent over him, and taking him in his arms, said, \u201cDo not be alarmed, for his life is in him.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 20:11","short":"Ac 20:11","text":"And when Paul had gone up and had broken bread and eaten, he conversed with them a long while, until daybreak, and so departed.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 20:12","short":"Ac 20:12","text":"And they took the youth away alive, and were not a little comforted.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 20:13","short":"Ac 20:13","text":"But going ahead to the ship, we set sail for Assos, intending to take Paul aboard there, for so he had arranged, intending himself to go by land.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 20:14","short":"Ac 20:14","text":"And when he met us at Assos, we took him on board and went to Mitylene.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 20:15","short":"Ac 20:15","text":"And sailing from there we came the following day opposite Chios; the next day we touched at Samos; and the day after that we went to Miletus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 20:16","short":"Ac 20:16","text":"For Paul had decided to sail past Ephesus, so that he might not have to spend time in Asia, for he was hastening to be at Jerusalem, if possible, on the day of Pentecost.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 20:17","short":"Ac 20:17","text":"Now from Miletus he sent to Ephesus and called the elders of the church to come to him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 20:18","short":"Ac 20:18","text":"And when they came to him, he said to them: \u201cYou yourselves know how I lived among you the whole time from the first day that I set foot in Asia,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 20:19","short":"Ac 20:19","text":"serving the Lord with all humility and with tears and with trials that happened to me through the plots of the Jews;","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 20:20","short":"Ac 20:20","text":"how I did not shrink from declaring to you anything that was profitable, and teaching you in public and from house to house,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 20:21","short":"Ac 20:21","text":"testifying both to Jews and to Greeks of repentance toward God and of faith in our Lord Jesus Christ.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 20:22","short":"Ac 20:22","text":"And now, behold, I am going to Jerusalem, constrained by the Spirit, not knowing what will happen to me there,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 20:23","short":"Ac 20:23","text":"except that the Holy Spirit testifies to me in every city that imprisonment and afflictions await me.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 20:24","short":"Ac 20:24","text":"But I do not account my life of any value nor as precious to myself, if only I may finish my course and the ministry that I received from the Lord Jesus, to testify to the gospel of the grace of God.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 20:25","short":"Ac 20:25","text":"And now, behold, I know that none of you among whom I have gone about proclaiming the kingdom will see my face again.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 20:26","short":"Ac 20:26","text":"Therefore I testify to you this day that I am innocent of the blood of all,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 20:27","short":"Ac 20:27","text":"for I did not shrink from declaring to you the whole counsel of God.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 20:28","short":"Ac 20:28","text":"Pay careful attention to yourselves and to all the flock, in which the Holy Spirit has made you overseers, to care for the church of God, which he obtained with his own blood.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 20:29","short":"Ac 20:29","text":"I know that after my departure fierce wolves will come in among you, not sparing the flock;","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":29},{"ref":"Acts 20:30","short":"Ac 20:30","text":"and from among your own selves will arise men speaking twisted things, to draw away the disciples after them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":30},{"ref":"Acts 20:31","short":"Ac 20:31","text":"Therefore be alert, remembering that for three years I did not cease night or day to admonish every one with tears.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":31},{"ref":"Acts 20:32","short":"Ac 20:32","text":"And now I commend you to God and to the word of his grace, which is able to build you up and to give you the inheritance among all those who are sanctified.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":32},{"ref":"Acts 20:33","short":"Ac 20:33","text":"I coveted no one\u2019s silver or gold or apparel.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":33},{"ref":"Acts 20:34","short":"Ac 20:34","text":"You yourselves know that these hands ministered to my necessities and to those who were with me.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":34},{"ref":"Acts 20:35","short":"Ac 20:35","text":"In all things I have shown you that by working hard in this way we must help the weak and remember the words of the Lord Jesus, how he himself said, \u2018It is more blessed to give than to receive.\u2019\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":35},{"ref":"Acts 20:36","short":"Ac 20:36","text":"And when he had said these things, he knelt down and prayed with them all.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":36},{"ref":"Acts 20:37","short":"Ac 20:37","text":"And there was much weeping on the part of all; they embraced Paul and kissed him,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":37},{"ref":"Acts 20:38","short":"Ac 20:38","text":"being sorrowful most of all because of the word he had spoken, that they would not see his face again. And they accompanied him to the ship.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_20.html","book":"Acts","ch":20,"v":38},{"ref":"Acts 21:1","short":"Ac 21:1","text":"And when we had parted from them and set sail, we came by a straight course to Cos, and the next day to Rhodes, and from there to Patara.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 21:2","short":"Ac 21:2","text":"And having found a ship crossing to Phoenicia, we went aboard and set sail.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 21:3","short":"Ac 21:3","text":"When we had come in sight of Cyprus, leaving it on the left we sailed to Syria and landed at Tyre, for there the ship was to unload its cargo.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 21:4","short":"Ac 21:4","text":"And having sought out the disciples, we stayed there for seven days. And through the Spirit they were telling Paul not to go on to Jerusalem.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 21:5","short":"Ac 21:5","text":"When our days there were ended, we departed and went on our journey, and they all, with wives and children, accompanied us until we were outside the city. And kneeling down on the beach, we prayed","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 21:6","short":"Ac 21:6","text":"and said farewell to one another. Then we went on board the ship, and they returned home.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 21:7","short":"Ac 21:7","text":"When we had finished the voyage from Tyre, we arrived at Ptolemais, and we greeted the brothers and stayed with them for one day.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 21:8","short":"Ac 21:8","text":"On the next day we departed and came to Caesarea, and we entered the house of Philip the evangelist, who was one of the seven, and stayed with him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 21:9","short":"Ac 21:9","text":"He had four unmarried daughters, who prophesied.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 21:10","short":"Ac 21:10","text":"While we were staying for many days, a prophet named Agabus came down from Judea.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 21:11","short":"Ac 21:11","text":"And coming to us, he took Paul\u2019s belt and bound his own feet and hands and said, \u201cThus says the Holy Spirit, \u2018This is how the Jews at Jerusalem will bind the man who owns this belt and deliver him into the hands of the Gentiles.\u2019\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 21:12","short":"Ac 21:12","text":"When we heard this, we and the people there urged him not to go up to Jerusalem.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 21:13","short":"Ac 21:13","text":"Then Paul answered, \u201cWhat are you doing, weeping and breaking my heart? For I am ready not only to be imprisoned but even to die in Jerusalem for the name of the Lord Jesus.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 21:14","short":"Ac 21:14","text":"And since he would not be persuaded, we ceased and said, \u201cLet the will of the Lord be done.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 21:15","short":"Ac 21:15","text":"After these days we got ready and went up to Jerusalem.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 21:16","short":"Ac 21:16","text":"And some of the disciples from Caesarea went with us, bringing us to the house of Mnason of Cyprus, an early disciple, with whom we should lodge.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 21:17","short":"Ac 21:17","text":"When we had come to Jerusalem, the brothers received us gladly.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 21:18","short":"Ac 21:18","text":"On the following day Paul went in with us to James, and all the elders were present.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 21:19","short":"Ac 21:19","text":"After greeting them, he related one by one the things that God had done among the Gentiles through his ministry.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 21:20","short":"Ac 21:20","text":"And when they heard it, they glorified God. And they said to him, \u201cYou see, brother, how many thousands there are among the Jews of those who have believed. They are all zealous for the law,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 21:21","short":"Ac 21:21","text":"and they have been told about you that you teach all the Jews who are among the Gentiles to forsake Moses, telling them not to circumcise their children or walk according to our customs.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 21:22","short":"Ac 21:22","text":"What then is to be done? They will certainly hear that you have come.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 21:23","short":"Ac 21:23","text":"Do therefore what we tell you. We have four men who are under a vow;","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 21:24","short":"Ac 21:24","text":"take these men and purify yourself along with them and pay their expenses, so that they may shave their heads. Thus all will know that there is nothing in what they have been told about you, but that you yourself also live in observance of the law.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 21:25","short":"Ac 21:25","text":"But as for the Gentiles who have believed, we have sent a letter with our judgment that they should abstain from what has been sacrificed to idols, and from blood, and from what has been strangled, and from sexual immorality.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 21:26","short":"Ac 21:26","text":"Then Paul took the men, and the next day he purified himself along with them and went into the temple, giving notice when the days of purification would be fulfilled and the offering presented for each one of them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 21:27","short":"Ac 21:27","text":"When the seven days were almost completed, the Jews from Asia, seeing him in the temple, stirred up the whole crowd and laid hands on him,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 21:28","short":"Ac 21:28","text":"crying out, \u201cMen of Israel, help! This is the man who is teaching everyone everywhere against the people and the law and this place. Moreover, he even brought Greeks into the temple and has defiled this holy place.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 21:29","short":"Ac 21:29","text":"For they had previously seen Trophimus the Ephesian with him in the city, and they supposed that Paul had brought him into the temple.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":29},{"ref":"Acts 21:30","short":"Ac 21:30","text":"Then all the city was stirred up, and the people ran together. They seized Paul and dragged him out of the temple, and at once the gates were shut.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":30},{"ref":"Acts 21:31","short":"Ac 21:31","text":"And as they were seeking to kill him, word came to the tribune of the cohort that all Jerusalem was in confusion.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":31},{"ref":"Acts 21:32","short":"Ac 21:32","text":"He at once took soldiers and centurions and ran down to them. And when they saw the tribune and the soldiers, they stopped beating Paul.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":32},{"ref":"Acts 21:33","short":"Ac 21:33","text":"Then the tribune came up and arrested him and ordered him to be bound with two chains. He inquired who he was and what he had done.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":33},{"ref":"Acts 21:34","short":"Ac 21:34","text":"Some in the crowd were shouting one thing, some another. And as he could not learn the facts because of the uproar, he ordered him to be brought into the barracks.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":34},{"ref":"Acts 21:35","short":"Ac 21:35","text":"And when he came to the steps, he was actually carried by the soldiers because of the violence of the crowd,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":35},{"ref":"Acts 21:36","short":"Ac 21:36","text":"for the mob of the people followed, crying out, \u201cAway with him!\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":36},{"ref":"Acts 21:37","short":"Ac 21:37","text":"As Paul was about to be brought into the barracks, he said to the tribune, \u201cMay I say something to you?\u201d And he said, \u201cDo you know Greek?","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":37},{"ref":"Acts 21:38","short":"Ac 21:38","text":"Are you not the Egyptian, then, who recently stirred up a revolt and led the four thousand men of the Assassins out into the wilderness?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":38},{"ref":"Acts 21:39","short":"Ac 21:39","text":"Paul replied, \u201cI am a Jew, from Tarsus in Cilicia, a citizen of no obscure city. I beg you, permit me to speak to the people.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":39},{"ref":"Acts 21:40","short":"Ac 21:40","text":"And when he had given him permission, Paul, standing on the steps, motioned with his hand to the people. And when there was a great hush, he addressed them in the Hebrew language, saying:","url":"nt/acts/Acts_21.html","book":"Acts","ch":21,"v":40},{"ref":"Acts 22:1","short":"Ac 22:1","text":"\u201cBrothers and fathers, hear the defense that I now make before you.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 22:2","short":"Ac 22:2","text":"And when they heard that he was addressing them in the Hebrew language, they became even more quiet. And he said:","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 22:3","short":"Ac 22:3","text":"\u201cI am a Jew, born in Tarsus in Cilicia, but brought up in this city, educated at the feet of Gamaliel according to the strict manner of the law of our fathers, being zealous for God as all of you are this day.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 22:4","short":"Ac 22:4","text":"I persecuted this Way to the death, binding and delivering to prison both men and women,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 22:5","short":"Ac 22:5","text":"as the high priest and the whole council of elders can bear me witness. From them I received letters to the brothers, and I journeyed toward Damascus to take those also who were there and bring them in bonds to Jerusalem to be punished.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 22:6","short":"Ac 22:6","text":"\u201cAs I was on my way and drew near to Damascus, about noon a great light from heaven suddenly shone around me.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 22:7","short":"Ac 22:7","text":"And I fell to the ground and heard a voice saying to me, \u2018Saul, Saul, why are you persecuting me?\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 22:8","short":"Ac 22:8","text":"And I answered, \u2018Who are you, Lord?\u2019 And he said to me, \u2018I am Jesus of Nazareth, whom you are persecuting.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 22:9","short":"Ac 22:9","text":"Now those who were with me saw the light but did not understand the voice of the one who was speaking to me.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 22:10","short":"Ac 22:10","text":"And I said, \u2018What shall I do, Lord?\u2019 And the Lord said to me, \u2018Rise, and go into Damascus, and there you will be told all that is appointed for you to do.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 22:11","short":"Ac 22:11","text":"And since I could not see because of the brightness of that light, I was led by the hand by those who were with me, and came into Damascus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 22:12","short":"Ac 22:12","text":"\u201cAnd one Ananias, a devout man according to the law, well spoken of by all the Jews who lived there,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 22:13","short":"Ac 22:13","text":"came to me, and standing by me said to me, \u2018Brother Saul, receive your sight.\u2019 And at that very hour I received my sight and saw him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 22:14","short":"Ac 22:14","text":"And he said, \u2018The God of our fathers appointed you to know his will, to see the Righteous One and to hear a voice from his mouth;","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 22:15","short":"Ac 22:15","text":"for you will be a witness for him to everyone of what you have seen and heard.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 22:16","short":"Ac 22:16","text":"And now why do you wait? Rise and be baptized and wash away your sins, calling on his name.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 22:17","short":"Ac 22:17","text":"\u201cWhen I had returned to Jerusalem and was praying in the temple, I fell into a trance","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 22:18","short":"Ac 22:18","text":"and saw him saying to me, \u2018Make haste and get out of Jerusalem quickly, because they will not accept your testimony about me.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 22:19","short":"Ac 22:19","text":"And I said, \u2018Lord, they themselves know that in one synagogue after another I imprisoned and beat those who believed in you.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 22:20","short":"Ac 22:20","text":"And when the blood of Stephen your witness was being shed, I myself was standing by and approving and watching over the garments of those who killed him.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 22:21","short":"Ac 22:21","text":"And he said to me, \u2018Go, for I will send you far away to the Gentiles.\u2019\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 22:22","short":"Ac 22:22","text":"Up to this word they listened to him. Then they raised their voices and said, \u201cAway with such a fellow from the earth! For he should not be allowed to live.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 22:23","short":"Ac 22:23","text":"And as they were shouting and throwing off their cloaks and flinging dust into the air,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 22:24","short":"Ac 22:24","text":"the tribune ordered him to be brought into the barracks, saying that he should be examined by flogging, to find out why they were shouting against him like this.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 22:25","short":"Ac 22:25","text":"But when they had stretched him out for the whips, Paul said to the centurion who was standing by, \u201cIs it lawful for you to flog a man who is a Roman citizen and uncondemned?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 22:26","short":"Ac 22:26","text":"When the centurion heard this, he went to the tribune and said to him, \u201cWhat are you about to do? For this man is a Roman citizen.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 22:27","short":"Ac 22:27","text":"So the tribune came and said to him, \u201cTell me, are you a Roman citizen?\u201d And he said, \u201cYes.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 22:28","short":"Ac 22:28","text":"The tribune answered, \u201cI bought this citizenship for a large sum.\u201d Paul said, \u201cBut I am a citizen by birth.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 22:29","short":"Ac 22:29","text":"So those who were about to examine him withdrew from him immediately, and the tribune also was afraid, for he realized that Paul was a Roman citizen and that he had bound him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":29},{"ref":"Acts 22:30","short":"Ac 22:30","text":"But on the next day, desiring to know the real reason why he was being accused by the Jews, he unbound him and commanded the chief priests and all the council to meet, and he brought Paul down and set him before them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_22.html","book":"Acts","ch":22,"v":30},{"ref":"Acts 23:1","short":"Ac 23:1","text":"And looking intently at the council, Paul said, \u201cBrothers, I have lived my life before God in all good conscience up to this day.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 23:2","short":"Ac 23:2","text":"And the high priest Ananias commanded those who stood by him to strike him on the mouth.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 23:3","short":"Ac 23:3","text":"Then Paul said to him, \u201cGod is going to strike you, you whitewashed wall! Are you sitting to judge me according to the law, and yet contrary to the law you order me to be struck?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 23:4","short":"Ac 23:4","text":"Those who stood by said, \u201cWould you revile God\u2019s high priest?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 23:5","short":"Ac 23:5","text":"And Paul said, \u201cI did not know, brothers, that he was the high priest, for it is written, \u2018You shall not speak evil of a ruler of your people.\u2019\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 23:6","short":"Ac 23:6","text":"Now when Paul perceived that one part were Sadducees and the other Pharisees, he cried out in the council, \u201cBrothers, I am a Pharisee, a son of Pharisees. It is with respect to the hope and the resurrection of the dead that I am on trial.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 23:7","short":"Ac 23:7","text":"And when he had said this, a dissension arose between the Pharisees and the Sadducees, and the assembly was divided.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 23:8","short":"Ac 23:8","text":"For the Sadducees say that there is no resurrection, nor angel, nor spirit, but the Pharisees acknowledge them all.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 23:9","short":"Ac 23:9","text":"Then a great clamor arose, and some of the scribes of the Pharisees\u2019 party stood up and contended sharply, \u201cWe find nothing wrong in this man. What if a spirit or an angel spoke to him?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 23:10","short":"Ac 23:10","text":"And when the dissension became violent, the tribune, afraid that Paul would be torn to pieces by them, commanded the soldiers to go down and take him away from among them by force and bring him into the barracks.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 23:11","short":"Ac 23:11","text":"The following night the Lord stood by him and said, \u201cTake courage, for as you have testified to the facts about me in Jerusalem, so you must testify also in Rome.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 23:12","short":"Ac 23:12","text":"When it was day, the Jews made a plot and bound themselves by an oath neither to eat nor drink till they had killed Paul.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 23:13","short":"Ac 23:13","text":"There were more than forty who made this conspiracy.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 23:14","short":"Ac 23:14","text":"They went to the chief priests and elders and said, \u201cWe have strictly bound ourselves by an oath to taste no food till we have killed Paul.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 23:15","short":"Ac 23:15","text":"Now therefore you, along with the council, give notice to the tribune to bring him down to you, as though you were going to determine his case more exactly. And we are ready to kill him before he comes near.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 23:16","short":"Ac 23:16","text":"Now the son of Paul\u2019s sister heard of their ambush, so he went and entered the barracks and told Paul.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 23:17","short":"Ac 23:17","text":"Paul called one of the centurions and said, \u201cTake this young man to the tribune, for he has something to tell him.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 23:18","short":"Ac 23:18","text":"So he took him and brought him to the tribune and said, \u201cPaul the prisoner called me and asked me to bring this young man to you, as he has something to say to you.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 23:19","short":"Ac 23:19","text":"The tribune took him by the hand, and going aside asked him privately, \u201cWhat is it that you have to tell me?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 23:20","short":"Ac 23:20","text":"And he said, \u201cThe Jews have agreed to ask you to bring Paul down to the council tomorrow, as though they were going to inquire somewhat more closely about him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 23:21","short":"Ac 23:21","text":"But do not be persuaded by them, for more than forty of their men are lying in ambush for him, who have bound themselves by an oath neither to eat nor drink till they have killed him. And now they are ready, waiting for your consent.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 23:22","short":"Ac 23:22","text":"So the tribune dismissed the young man, charging him, \u201cTell no one that you have informed me of these things.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 23:23","short":"Ac 23:23","text":"Then he called two of the centurions and said, \u201cGet ready two hundred soldiers, with seventy horsemen and two hundred spearmen to go as far as Caesarea at the third hour of the night.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 23:24","short":"Ac 23:24","text":"Also provide mounts for Paul to ride and bring him safely to Felix the governor.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 23:25","short":"Ac 23:25","text":"And he wrote a letter to this effect:","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 23:26","short":"Ac 23:26","text":"\u201cClaudius Lysias, to his Excellency the governor Felix, greetings.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 23:27","short":"Ac 23:27","text":"This man was seized by the Jews and was about to be killed by them when I came upon them with the soldiers and rescued him, having learned that he was a Roman citizen.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 23:28","short":"Ac 23:28","text":"And desiring to know the charge for which they were accusing him, I brought him down to their council.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 23:29","short":"Ac 23:29","text":"I found that he was being accused about questions of their law, but charged with nothing deserving death or imprisonment.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":29},{"ref":"Acts 23:30","short":"Ac 23:30","text":"And when it was disclosed to me that there would be a plot against the man, I sent him to you at once, ordering his accusers also to state before you what they have against him.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":30},{"ref":"Acts 23:31","short":"Ac 23:31","text":"So the soldiers, according to their instructions, took Paul and brought him by night to Antipatris.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":31},{"ref":"Acts 23:32","short":"Ac 23:32","text":"And on the next day they returned to the barracks, letting the horsemen go on with him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":32},{"ref":"Acts 23:33","short":"Ac 23:33","text":"When they had come to Caesarea and delivered the letter to the governor, they presented Paul also before him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":33},{"ref":"Acts 23:34","short":"Ac 23:34","text":"On reading the letter, he asked what province he was from. And when he learned that he was from Cilicia,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":34},{"ref":"Acts 23:35","short":"Ac 23:35","text":"he said, \u201cI will give you a hearing when your accusers arrive.\u201d And he commanded him to be guarded in Herod\u2019s praetorium.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_23.html","book":"Acts","ch":23,"v":35},{"ref":"Acts 24:1","short":"Ac 24:1","text":"And after five days the high priest Ananias came down with some elders and a spokesman, one Tertullus. They laid before the governor their case against Paul.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 24:2","short":"Ac 24:2","text":"And when he had been summoned, Tertullus began to accuse him, saying: \u201cSince through you we enjoy much peace, and since by your foresight, most excellent Felix, reforms are being made for this nation,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 24:3","short":"Ac 24:3","text":"in every way and everywhere we accept this with all gratitude.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 24:4","short":"Ac 24:4","text":"But, to detain you no further, I beg you in your kindness to hear us briefly.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 24:5","short":"Ac 24:5","text":"For we have found this man a plague, one who stirs up riots among all the Jews throughout the world and is a ringleader of the sect of the Nazarenes.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 24:6","short":"Ac 24:6","text":"He even tried to profane the temple, but we seized him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 24:8","short":"Ac 24:8","text":"By examining him yourself you will be able to find out from him about everything of which we accuse him.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 24:9","short":"Ac 24:9","text":"The Jews also joined in the charge, affirming that all these things were so.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 24:10","short":"Ac 24:10","text":"And when the governor had nodded to him to speak, Paul replied: \u201cKnowing that for many years you have been a judge over this nation, I cheerfully make my defense.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 24:11","short":"Ac 24:11","text":"You can verify that it is not more than twelve days since I went up to worship in Jerusalem,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 24:12","short":"Ac 24:12","text":"and they did not find me disputing with anyone or stirring up a crowd, either in the temple or in the synagogues or in the city.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 24:13","short":"Ac 24:13","text":"Neither can they prove to you what they now bring up against me.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 24:14","short":"Ac 24:14","text":"But this I confess to you, that according to the Way, which they call a sect, I worship the God of our fathers, believing everything laid down by the Law and written in the Prophets,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 24:15","short":"Ac 24:15","text":"having a hope in God, which these men themselves accept, that there will be a resurrection of both the just and the unjust.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 24:16","short":"Ac 24:16","text":"So I always take pains to have a clear conscience toward both God and man.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 24:17","short":"Ac 24:17","text":"Now after several years I came to bring alms to my nation and to present offerings.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 24:18","short":"Ac 24:18","text":"While I was doing this, they found me purified in the temple, without any crowd or tumult. But some Jews from Asia\u2014","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 24:19","short":"Ac 24:19","text":"they ought to be here before you and to make an accusation, should they have anything against me.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 24:20","short":"Ac 24:20","text":"Or else let these men themselves say what wrongdoing they found when I stood before the council,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 24:21","short":"Ac 24:21","text":"other than this one thing that I cried out while standing among them: \u2018It is with respect to the resurrection of the dead that I am on trial before you this day.\u2019\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 24:22","short":"Ac 24:22","text":"But Felix, having a rather accurate knowledge of the Way, put them off, saying, \u201cWhen Lysias the tribune comes down, I will decide your case.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 24:23","short":"Ac 24:23","text":"Then he gave orders to the centurion that he should be kept in custody but have some liberty, and that none of his friends should be prevented from attending to his needs.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 24:24","short":"Ac 24:24","text":"After some days Felix came with his wife Drusilla, who was Jewish, and he sent for Paul and heard him speak about faith in Christ Jesus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 24:25","short":"Ac 24:25","text":"And as he reasoned about righteousness and self-control and the coming judgment, Felix was alarmed and said, \u201cGo away for the present. When I get an opportunity I will summon you.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 24:26","short":"Ac 24:26","text":"At the same time he hoped that money would be given him by Paul. So he sent for him often and conversed with him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 24:27","short":"Ac 24:27","text":"When two years had elapsed, Felix was succeeded by Porcius Festus. And desiring to do the Jews a favor, Felix left Paul in prison.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_24.html","book":"Acts","ch":24,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 25:1","short":"Ac 25:1","text":"Now three days after Festus had arrived in the province, he went up to Jerusalem from Caesarea.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 25:2","short":"Ac 25:2","text":"And the chief priests and the principal men of the Jews laid out their case against Paul, and they urged him,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 25:3","short":"Ac 25:3","text":"asking as a favor against Paul that he summon him to Jerusalem\u2014because they were planning an ambush to kill him on the way.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 25:4","short":"Ac 25:4","text":"Festus replied that Paul was being kept at Caesarea and that he himself intended to go there shortly.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 25:5","short":"Ac 25:5","text":"\u201cSo,\u201d said he, \u201clet the men of authority among you go down with me, and if there is anything wrong about the man, let them bring charges against him.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 25:6","short":"Ac 25:6","text":"After he stayed among them not more than eight or ten days, he went down to Caesarea. And the next day he took his seat on the tribunal and ordered Paul to be brought.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 25:7","short":"Ac 25:7","text":"When he had arrived, the Jews who had come down from Jerusalem stood around him, bringing many and serious charges against him that they could not prove.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 25:8","short":"Ac 25:8","text":"Paul argued in his defense, \u201cNeither against the law of the Jews, nor against the temple, nor against Caesar have I committed any offense.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 25:9","short":"Ac 25:9","text":"But Festus, wishing to do the Jews a favor, said to Paul, \u201cDo you wish to go up to Jerusalem and there be tried on these charges before me?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 25:10","short":"Ac 25:10","text":"But Paul said, \u201cI am standing before Caesar\u2019s tribunal, where I ought to be tried. To the Jews I have done no wrong, as you yourself know very well.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 25:11","short":"Ac 25:11","text":"If then I am a wrongdoer and have committed anything for which I deserve to die, I do not seek to escape death. But if there is nothing to their charges against me, no one can give me up to them. I appeal to Caesar.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 25:12","short":"Ac 25:12","text":"Then Festus, when he had conferred with his council, answered, \u201cTo Caesar you have appealed; to Caesar you shall go.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 25:13","short":"Ac 25:13","text":"Now when some days had passed, Agrippa the king and Bernice arrived at Caesarea and greeted Festus.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 25:14","short":"Ac 25:14","text":"And as they stayed there many days, Festus laid Paul\u2019s case before the king, saying, \u201cThere is a man left prisoner by Felix,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 25:15","short":"Ac 25:15","text":"and when I was at Jerusalem, the chief priests and the elders of the Jews laid out their case against him, asking for a sentence of condemnation against him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 25:16","short":"Ac 25:16","text":"I answered them that it was not the custom of the Romans to give up anyone before the accused met the accusers face to face and had opportunity to make his defense concerning the charge laid against him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 25:17","short":"Ac 25:17","text":"So when they came together here, I made no delay, but on the next day took my seat on the tribunal and ordered the man to be brought.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 25:18","short":"Ac 25:18","text":"When the accusers stood up, they brought no charge in his case of such evils as I supposed.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 25:19","short":"Ac 25:19","text":"Rather they had certain points of dispute with him about their own religion and about a certain Jesus, who was dead, but whom Paul asserted to be alive.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 25:20","short":"Ac 25:20","text":"Being at a loss how to investigate these questions, I asked whether he wanted to go to Jerusalem and be tried there regarding them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 25:21","short":"Ac 25:21","text":"But when Paul had appealed to be kept in custody for the decision of the emperor, I ordered him to be held until I could send him to Caesar.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 25:22","short":"Ac 25:22","text":"Then Agrippa said to Festus, \u201cI would like to hear the man myself.\u201d \u201cTomorrow,\u201d said he, \u201cyou will hear him.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 25:23","short":"Ac 25:23","text":"So on the next day Agrippa and Bernice came with great pomp, and they entered the audience hall with the military tribunes and the prominent men of the city. Then, at the command of Festus, Paul was brought in.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 25:24","short":"Ac 25:24","text":"And Festus said, \u201cKing Agrippa and all who are present with us, you see this man about whom the whole Jewish people petitioned me, both in Jerusalem and here, shouting that he ought not to live any longer.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 25:25","short":"Ac 25:25","text":"But I found that he had done nothing deserving death. And as he himself appealed to the emperor, I decided to go ahead and send him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 25:26","short":"Ac 25:26","text":"But I have nothing definite to write to my lord about him. Therefore I have brought him before you all, and especially before you, King Agrippa, so that, after we have examined him, I may have something to write.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 25:27","short":"Ac 25:27","text":"For it seems to me unreasonable, in sending a prisoner, not to indicate the charges against him.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_25.html","book":"Acts","ch":25,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 26:1","short":"Ac 26:1","text":"So Agrippa said to Paul, \u201cYou have permission to speak for yourself.\u201d Then Paul stretched out his hand and made his defense:","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 26:2","short":"Ac 26:2","text":"\u201cI consider myself fortunate that it is before you, King Agrippa, I am going to make my defense today against all the accusations of the Jews,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 26:3","short":"Ac 26:3","text":"especially because you are familiar with all the customs and controversies of the Jews. Therefore I beg you to listen to me patiently.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 26:4","short":"Ac 26:4","text":"\u201cMy manner of life from my youth, spent from the beginning among my own nation and in Jerusalem, is known by all the Jews.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 26:5","short":"Ac 26:5","text":"They have known for a long time, if they are willing to testify, that according to the strictest party of our religion I have lived as a Pharisee.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 26:6","short":"Ac 26:6","text":"And now I stand here on trial because of my hope in the promise made by God to our fathers,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 26:7","short":"Ac 26:7","text":"to which our twelve tribes hope to attain, as they earnestly worship night and day. And for this hope I am accused by Jews, O king!","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 26:8","short":"Ac 26:8","text":"Why is it thought incredible by any of you that God raises the dead?","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 26:9","short":"Ac 26:9","text":"\u201cI myself was convinced that I ought to do many things in opposing the name of Jesus of Nazareth.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 26:10","short":"Ac 26:10","text":"And I did so in Jerusalem. I not only locked up many of the saints in prison after receiving authority from the chief priests, but when they were put to death I cast my vote against them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 26:11","short":"Ac 26:11","text":"And I punished them often in all the synagogues and tried to make them blaspheme, and in raging fury against them I persecuted them even to foreign cities.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 26:12","short":"Ac 26:12","text":"\u201cIn this connection I journeyed to Damascus with the authority and commission of the chief priests.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 26:13","short":"Ac 26:13","text":"At midday, O king, I saw on the way a light from heaven, brighter than the sun, that shone around me and those who journeyed with me.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 26:14","short":"Ac 26:14","text":"And when we had all fallen to the ground, I heard a voice saying to me in the Hebrew language, \u2018Saul, Saul, why are you persecuting me? It is hard for you to kick against the goads.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 26:15","short":"Ac 26:15","text":"And I said, \u2018Who are you, Lord?\u2019 And the Lord said, \u2018I am Jesus whom you are persecuting.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 26:16","short":"Ac 26:16","text":"But rise and stand upon your feet, for I have appeared to you for this purpose, to appoint you as a servant and witness to the things in which you have seen me and to those in which I will appear to you,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 26:17","short":"Ac 26:17","text":"delivering you from your people and from the Gentiles\u2014to whom I am sending you","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 26:18","short":"Ac 26:18","text":"to open their eyes, so that they may turn from darkness to light and from the power of Satan to God, that they may receive forgiveness of sins and a place among those who are sanctified by faith in me.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 26:19","short":"Ac 26:19","text":"\u201cTherefore, O King Agrippa, I was not disobedient to the heavenly vision,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 26:20","short":"Ac 26:20","text":"but declared first to those in Damascus, then in Jerusalem and throughout all the region of Judea, and also to the Gentiles, that they should repent and turn to God, performing deeds in keeping with their repentance.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 26:21","short":"Ac 26:21","text":"For this reason the Jews seized me in the temple and tried to kill me.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 26:22","short":"Ac 26:22","text":"To this day I have had the help that comes from God, and so I stand here testifying both to small and great, saying nothing but what the prophets and Moses said would come to pass:","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 26:23","short":"Ac 26:23","text":"that the Christ must suffer and that, by being the first to rise from the dead, he would proclaim light both to our people and to the Gentiles.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 26:24","short":"Ac 26:24","text":"And as he was saying these things in his defense, Festus said with a loud voice, \u201cPaul, you are out of your mind; your great learning is driving you out of your mind.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 26:25","short":"Ac 26:25","text":"But Paul said, \u201cI am not out of my mind, most excellent Festus, but I am speaking true and rational words.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 26:26","short":"Ac 26:26","text":"For the king knows about these things, and to him I speak boldly. For I am persuaded that none of these things has escaped his notice, for this has not been done in a corner.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 26:27","short":"Ac 26:27","text":"King Agrippa, do you believe the prophets? I know that you believe.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 26:28","short":"Ac 26:28","text":"And Agrippa said to Paul, \u201cIn a short time would you persuade me to be a Christian?\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 26:29","short":"Ac 26:29","text":"And Paul said, \u201cWhether short or long, I would to God that not only you but also all who hear me this day might become such as I am\u2014except for these chains.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":29},{"ref":"Acts 26:30","short":"Ac 26:30","text":"Then the king rose, and the governor and Bernice and those who were sitting with them.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":30},{"ref":"Acts 26:31","short":"Ac 26:31","text":"And when they had withdrawn, they said to one another, \u201cThis man is doing nothing to deserve death or imprisonment.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":31},{"ref":"Acts 26:32","short":"Ac 26:32","text":"And Agrippa said to Festus, \u201cThis man could have been set free if he had not appealed to Caesar.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_26.html","book":"Acts","ch":26,"v":32},{"ref":"Acts 27:1","short":"Ac 27:1","text":"And when it was decided that we should sail for Italy, they delivered Paul and some other prisoners to a centurion of the Augustan Cohort named Julius.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 27:2","short":"Ac 27:2","text":"And embarking in a ship of Adramyttium, which was about to sail to the ports along the coast of Asia, we put to sea, accompanied by Aristarchus, a Macedonian from Thessalonica.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 27:3","short":"Ac 27:3","text":"The next day we put in at Sidon. And Julius treated Paul kindly and gave him leave to go to his friends and be cared for.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 27:4","short":"Ac 27:4","text":"And putting out to sea from there we sailed under the lee of Cyprus, because the winds were against us.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 27:5","short":"Ac 27:5","text":"And when we had sailed across the open sea along the coast of Cilicia and Pamphylia, we came to Myra in Lycia.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 27:6","short":"Ac 27:6","text":"There the centurion found a ship of Alexandria sailing for Italy and put us on board.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 27:7","short":"Ac 27:7","text":"We sailed slowly for a number of days and arrived with difficulty off Cnidus, and as the wind did not allow us to go farther, we sailed under the lee of Crete off Salmone.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 27:8","short":"Ac 27:8","text":"Coasting along it with difficulty, we came to a place called Fair Havens, near which was the city of Lasea.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 27:9","short":"Ac 27:9","text":"Since much time had passed, and the voyage was now dangerous because even the Fast was already over, Paul advised them,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 27:10","short":"Ac 27:10","text":"saying, \u201cSirs, I perceive that the voyage will be with injury and much loss, not only of the cargo and the ship, but also of our lives.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 27:11","short":"Ac 27:11","text":"But the centurion paid more attention to the pilot and to the owner of the ship than to what Paul said.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 27:12","short":"Ac 27:12","text":"And because the harbor was not suitable to spend the winter in, the majority decided to put out to sea from there, on the chance that somehow they could reach Phoenix, a harbor of Crete, facing both southwest and northwest, and spend the winter there.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 27:13","short":"Ac 27:13","text":"Now when the south wind blew gently, supposing that they had obtained their purpose, they weighed anchor and sailed along Crete, close to the shore.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 27:14","short":"Ac 27:14","text":"But soon a tempestuous wind, called the northeaster, struck down from the land.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 27:15","short":"Ac 27:15","text":"And when the ship was caught and could not face the wind, we gave way to it and were driven along.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 27:16","short":"Ac 27:16","text":"Running under the lee of a small island called Cauda, we managed with difficulty to secure the ship\u2019s boat.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 27:17","short":"Ac 27:17","text":"After hoisting it up, they used supports to undergird the ship. Then, fearing that they would run aground on the Syrtis, they lowered the gear, and thus they were driven along.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 27:18","short":"Ac 27:18","text":"Since we were violently storm-tossed, they began the next day to jettison the cargo.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 27:19","short":"Ac 27:19","text":"And on the third day they threw the ship\u2019s tackle overboard with their own hands.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 27:20","short":"Ac 27:20","text":"When neither sun nor stars appeared for many days, and no small tempest lay on us, all hope of our being saved was at last abandoned.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 27:21","short":"Ac 27:21","text":"Since they had been without food for a long time, Paul stood up among them and said, \u201cMen, you should have listened to me and not have set sail from Crete and incurred this injury and loss.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 27:22","short":"Ac 27:22","text":"Yet now I urge you to take heart, for there will be no loss of life among you, but only of the ship.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 27:23","short":"Ac 27:23","text":"For this very night there stood before me an angel of the God to whom I belong and whom I worship,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 27:24","short":"Ac 27:24","text":"and he said, \u2018Do not be afraid, Paul; you must stand before Caesar. And behold, God has granted you all those who sail with you.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 27:25","short":"Ac 27:25","text":"So take heart, men, for I have faith in God that it will be exactly as I have been told.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 27:26","short":"Ac 27:26","text":"But we must run aground on some island.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 27:27","short":"Ac 27:27","text":"When the fourteenth night had come, as we were being driven across the Adriatic Sea, about midnight the sailors suspected that they were nearing land.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 27:28","short":"Ac 27:28","text":"So they took a sounding and found twenty fathoms. A little farther on they took a sounding again and found fifteen fathoms.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 27:29","short":"Ac 27:29","text":"And fearing that we might run on the rocks, they let down four anchors from the stern and prayed for day to come.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":29},{"ref":"Acts 27:30","short":"Ac 27:30","text":"And as the sailors were seeking to escape from the ship, and had lowered the ship\u2019s boat into the sea under pretense of laying out anchors from the bow,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":30},{"ref":"Acts 27:31","short":"Ac 27:31","text":"Paul said to the centurion and the soldiers, \u201cUnless these men stay in the ship, you cannot be saved.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":31},{"ref":"Acts 27:32","short":"Ac 27:32","text":"Then the soldiers cut away the ropes of the ship\u2019s boat and let it go.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":32},{"ref":"Acts 27:33","short":"Ac 27:33","text":"As day was about to dawn, Paul urged them all to take some food, saying, \u201cToday is the fourteenth day that you have continued in suspense and without food, having taken nothing.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":33},{"ref":"Acts 27:34","short":"Ac 27:34","text":"Therefore I urge you to take some food. For it will give you strength, for not a hair is to perish from the head of any of you.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":34},{"ref":"Acts 27:35","short":"Ac 27:35","text":"And when he had said these things, he took bread, and giving thanks to God in the presence of all he broke it and began to eat.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":35},{"ref":"Acts 27:36","short":"Ac 27:36","text":"Then they all were encouraged and ate some food themselves.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":36},{"ref":"Acts 27:37","short":"Ac 27:37","text":"(We were in all 276 persons in the ship.)","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":37},{"ref":"Acts 27:38","short":"Ac 27:38","text":"And when they had eaten enough, they lightened the ship, throwing out the wheat into the sea.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":38},{"ref":"Acts 27:39","short":"Ac 27:39","text":"Now when it was day, they did not recognize the land, but they noticed a bay with a beach, on which they planned if possible to run the ship ashore.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":39},{"ref":"Acts 27:40","short":"Ac 27:40","text":"So they cast off the anchors and left them in the sea, at the same time loosening the ropes that tied the rudders. Then hoisting the foresail to the wind they made for the beach.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":40},{"ref":"Acts 27:41","short":"Ac 27:41","text":"But striking a reef, they ran the vessel aground. The bow stuck and remained immovable, and the stern was being broken up by the surf.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":41},{"ref":"Acts 27:42","short":"Ac 27:42","text":"The soldiers\u2019 plan was to kill the prisoners, lest any should swim away and escape.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":42},{"ref":"Acts 27:43","short":"Ac 27:43","text":"But the centurion, wishing to save Paul, kept them from carrying out their plan. He ordered those who could swim to jump overboard first and make for the land,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":43},{"ref":"Acts 27:44","short":"Ac 27:44","text":"and the rest on planks or on pieces of the ship. And so it was that all were brought safely to land.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_27.html","book":"Acts","ch":27,"v":44},{"ref":"Acts 28:1","short":"Ac 28:1","text":"After we were brought safely through, we then learned that the island was called Malta.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":1},{"ref":"Acts 28:2","short":"Ac 28:2","text":"The native people showed us unusual kindness, for they kindled a fire and welcomed us all, because it had begun to rain and was cold.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":2},{"ref":"Acts 28:3","short":"Ac 28:3","text":"When Paul had gathered a bundle of sticks and put them on the fire, a viper came out because of the heat and fastened on his hand.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":3},{"ref":"Acts 28:4","short":"Ac 28:4","text":"When the native people saw the creature hanging from his hand, they said to one another, \u201cNo doubt this man is a murderer. Though he has escaped from the sea, Justice has not allowed him to live.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":4},{"ref":"Acts 28:5","short":"Ac 28:5","text":"He, however, shook off the creature into the fire and suffered no harm.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":5},{"ref":"Acts 28:6","short":"Ac 28:6","text":"They were waiting for him to swell up or suddenly fall down dead. But when they had waited a long time and saw no misfortune come to him, they changed their minds and said that he was a god.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":6},{"ref":"Acts 28:7","short":"Ac 28:7","text":"Now in the neighborhood of that place were lands belonging to the chief man of the island, named Publius, who received us and entertained us hospitably for three days.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":7},{"ref":"Acts 28:8","short":"Ac 28:8","text":"It happened that the father of Publius lay sick with fever and dysentery. And Paul visited him and prayed, and putting his hands on him, healed him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":8},{"ref":"Acts 28:9","short":"Ac 28:9","text":"And when this had taken place, the rest of the people on the island who had diseases also came and were cured.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":9},{"ref":"Acts 28:10","short":"Ac 28:10","text":"They also honored us greatly, and when we were about to sail, they put on board whatever we needed.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":10},{"ref":"Acts 28:11","short":"Ac 28:11","text":"After three months we set sail in a ship that had wintered in the island, a ship of Alexandria, with the twin gods as a figurehead.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":11},{"ref":"Acts 28:12","short":"Ac 28:12","text":"Putting in at Syracuse, we stayed there for three days.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":12},{"ref":"Acts 28:13","short":"Ac 28:13","text":"And from there we made a circuit and arrived at Rhegium. And after one day a south wind sprang up, and on the second day we came to Puteoli.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":13},{"ref":"Acts 28:14","short":"Ac 28:14","text":"There we found brothers and were invited to stay with them for seven days. And so we came to Rome.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":14},{"ref":"Acts 28:15","short":"Ac 28:15","text":"And the brothers there, when they heard about us, came as far as the Forum of Appius and Three Taverns to meet us. On seeing them, Paul thanked God and took courage.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":15},{"ref":"Acts 28:16","short":"Ac 28:16","text":"And when we came into Rome, Paul was allowed to stay by himself, with the soldier who guarded him.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":16},{"ref":"Acts 28:17","short":"Ac 28:17","text":"After three days he called together the local leaders of the Jews, and when they had gathered, he said to them, \u201cBrothers, though I had done nothing against our people or the customs of our fathers, yet I was delivered as a prisoner from Jerusalem into the hands of the Romans.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":17},{"ref":"Acts 28:18","short":"Ac 28:18","text":"When they had examined me, they wished to set me at liberty, because there was no reason for the death penalty in my case.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":18},{"ref":"Acts 28:19","short":"Ac 28:19","text":"But because the Jews objected, I was compelled to appeal to Caesar\u2014though I had no charge to bring against my nation.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":19},{"ref":"Acts 28:20","short":"Ac 28:20","text":"For this reason, therefore, I have asked to see you and speak with you, since it is because of the hope of Israel that I am wearing this chain.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":20},{"ref":"Acts 28:21","short":"Ac 28:21","text":"And they said to him, \u201cWe have received no letters from Judea about you, and none of the brothers coming here has reported or spoken any evil about you.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":21},{"ref":"Acts 28:22","short":"Ac 28:22","text":"But we desire to hear from you what your views are, for with regard to this sect we know that everywhere it is spoken against.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":22},{"ref":"Acts 28:23","short":"Ac 28:23","text":"When they had appointed a day for him, they came to him at his lodging in greater numbers. From morning till evening he expounded to them, testifying to the kingdom of God and trying to convince them about Jesus both from the Law of Moses and from the Prophets.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":23},{"ref":"Acts 28:24","short":"Ac 28:24","text":"And some were convinced by what he said, but others disbelieved.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":24},{"ref":"Acts 28:25","short":"Ac 28:25","text":"And disagreeing among themselves, they departed after Paul had made one statement: \u201cThe Holy Spirit was right in saying to your fathers through Isaiah the prophet:","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":25},{"ref":"Acts 28:26","short":"Ac 28:26","text":"\u201c\u2018Go to this people, and say, \u201cYou will indeed hear but never understand, and you will indeed see but never perceive.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":26},{"ref":"Acts 28:27","short":"Ac 28:27","text":"For this people\u2019s heart has grown dull, and with their ears they can barely hear, and their eyes they have closed; lest they should see with their eyes and hear with their ears and understand with their heart and turn, and I would heal them.\u2019","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":27},{"ref":"Acts 28:28","short":"Ac 28:28","text":"Therefore let it be known to you that this salvation of God has been sent to the Gentiles; they will listen.\u201d","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":28},{"ref":"Acts 28:30","short":"Ac 28:30","text":"He lived there two whole years at his own expense, and welcomed all who came to him,","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":30},{"ref":"Acts 28:31","short":"Ac 28:31","text":"proclaiming the kingdom of God and teaching about the Lord Jesus Christ with all boldness and without hindrance.","url":"nt/acts/Acts_28.html","book":"Acts","ch":28,"v":31}];
if(!window.VERSES_ALL)window.VERSES_ALL=[];
window.VERSES_ALL=window.VERSES_ALL.concat(VERSES_ACTS);
